<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR="#090F7F"><H2>SPEAKING ENGAGEMENTS</H2></FONT>
</CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN="left" HSPACE="8" VSPACE="8" WIDTH="298" HEIGHT="208" SRC="art/vwalt.gif" ALT="Walter Cunningham">
<BR>

<IMG WIDTH="268" HEIGHT="87" SRC="art/smlogo.gif">
<H2>WALTER CUNNINGHAM</H2><P>
Mr. Cunningham may be contacted regarding his services as a lecturer and schedule of appearances by email at <A HREF="mailto:waltc@spacezone.com">waltc@spacezone.com.</A>
<P>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<P>
<H3>Professional Speaking Activities</H3>
<P>
Since becoming an Astronaut in 1963, I have had thousands of opportunities to speak or to make formal presentations or appearances.  Over the years, I developed a real enjoyment out of speaking in front of an audience. While pursuing a business career since 1971, I have continued to devote some time each year to professional speaking engagements.  These include appearances at national conventions, meetings of major corporations and organizations, venture capital industry conferences and even governmental organizations. Since a career as a venture capitalist limits my speaking engagements to less than ten appearances a year, I have elected to pursue this interest without an agent.
<P>
For the past several years, my topics have focused on three principal areas:  (1) The value of risk in the lives of individuals and companies, (2) Entrepreneurism and The Venture Capital Process for growing companies and (3) space related topics.  Given my Astronaut notoriety, there is some space content in all of my speeches.  The space related topics range from a Historical Perspective Of The U.S. Space Program, The Legacy of Apollo and the U.S. - Russian Space Race to a world wide travelogue of pictures taken from earth orbit.
<P>
My favorite topic is an inspirational speech drawing from my experiences in both business and space.  It is built around the theme: "The Chance of Dangerous Adventure" and what it brings to our lives in terms of responsibility, leadership and satisfaction.  I talk about moving a company or organization "beyond competition", drawing on examples from the manned space program -- from the disasters as well as the accomplishments.  I talk about finding frontiers in your own business and how to operate at the boundaries of those frontiers; of how to take your life into your own hands and create your own destiny. 
<P>
These appearances have been extremely well received over the years, eliciting many nice references. Bookings are made as much as one year in advance. Fees for appearances, in addition to expenses, range from $3,000 to $7,500, depending on the function, size of the audience and the location.  My preference is for audiences of influential, decision makers in a setting which allows relatively free, two-way exchange.
<P>

