<BR>
<H2>
<B>The American Space Odyssey Video Library</B></H2>
<P>


This thirty volume video series chronicles the history of the American Space program, from its inception over thirty years ago through the successful operation of the current space shuttle program. Each volume consists of original film and video footage from NASA. Every tape opens with a personal introduction by NASA mission astronauts, including Pete Conrad, Walt Cunningham, Charlie Duke, Rick Hauck, Bob Overmyer, Wally Schirra and Rusty Schweickart. 

<P>
