<!--Volume 1-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v1.jpg" ALT="Freedom 7">

<A NAME="v1"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Freedom 7</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Alan Shepard
<P>
In 1960, America was already studying weather tracking and radiation in outer space. Satellites and other sensitive equipment had been flown in orbit, and now it was time for man to follow.
<P>
This video shows you the original story of Freedom 7, America's first manned space flight. From the physical testing of astronauts to the structural testing of rockets, Freedom 7 was a breakthrough no space enthusiast should miss.
<P>

<A HREF="video/v1.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="38" SRC="art/film.gif">Freedom 7</A> - 3.5 MB QuickTime video
<BR>
<A HREF="v1.ram"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio</A> by astronaut Alan Shepard introducing <I>Freedom 7</I>.

