<!--Volume 2-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v2.jpg" ALT"Voyage of Friendship 7">

<A NAME="v2"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Voyage of Friendship 7</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Wally Schirra
<P>
America's Mercury program paved the way for Gemini, Apollo and more. It was the time when spaceflight was invented, and as America's engineers, astronauts, scientists improved safety technology, they reached further into the unknown.
<P>
The exciting video unfolds the story of the Friendship 7 mission. John Glenn was the first American to orbit the earth and he did so in just 88 minutes. It was a heroic episode in our history. And the first step in a long walk we would take into outer space.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="video/v2.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="38" SRC="art/film.gif">Voyage of Friendship 7</A> - 4.8 MB QuickTime
