<!--Volume 4-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg" ALT="Four Days of Gemini 4">

<A NAME="v4"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Four Days of Gemini 4</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Pete Conrad
<P>
America was really "into" space following the triumphs of the Mercury missions. EVA or Extra Vehicular Activity, was a buzzword of the time meaning: spacewalk. America would perform their first EVA during the four days of Gemini 4.
<P>
This video is the story of America's first spacewalk. Beautiful photos and air-to-ground communications tell the story of man and machine floating in outer space. You'll see revolutionary materials developed for the special spacesuits needed. Plus, you'll get a glimpse of an early computer which could barely compete with today's calculators. Enjoy this NASA documentary of the four days of Gemini 4.
<P>

<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="38" SRC="art/film.gif">Four Days of Gemini 4,  QuickTime sample available soon.
<BR>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio Sample available soon.

