<!--Volume 5-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg" ALT="This is Houston, Flight">

<A NAME="v5"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>This is Houston, Flight</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut <A HREF="walt.htm">Walt Cunningham</A>
<P>
This film shows you how careful NASA is when testing and training for missions. Astronauts and equipment are put through endless rescue simulations and performance tests. Even with a year of pre-flight preparation, they can't prepare for the unexpected.
<P>
Gemini 8 recorded the first docking with an unmanned spaceship but the mission was cut short. A thruster had fouled causing both spacecraft to spin. Once separated, the astronauts determined it was the Gemini booster that had the problem. They had to use reentry engines to stabilize which prompted a hasty return to Earth. Watch this narrow escape aboard the Gemini 8.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="38" SRC="art/film.gif">This is Houston, Flight, QuickTime sample available soon.
<BR>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio Sample available soon.

