<!--Volume 7-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v7.jpg">

<A NAME="v7"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>The Eagle Has Landed</B></FONT></A>

<P>
<B>Awards</B><BR>
<I>Certificate of Exhibition, Edinburgh Film Festival, 1969<P>
Certificate of Merit, American Science Film Association, 1969</I>
<P>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Alan Shepard

<P>
An estimated one billion people watched as Neil Armstrong set foot on the moon. America had made a giant step for science, and the entire world. 
<P>
This ward winning video showcases Apollo 11, the mission that put man on the moon. You&#39;ll see close-ups of the moon&#39;s surface, just as Americans and the world, had been the first to see in 1969. You&#39;ll watch as the whole world cheered their return, including President Richard Nixon. Feel the excitement in the video everyone should see.

