<!--Volume 9-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg">

<A NAME="v9"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Moon, Old and New</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
30 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Rick Hauck
<P>
<P>
<B>Awards</B><BR>
<I>Golden Eagle, Council on International Nontheatrical Events (CINE), 1971<P>
5th International Review of Didactic Films, Rome<P>
3rd International Review of TV Educational Films, Rome Fair, 1971<P>
</I>
<P>
Fairytales and fiction have surrounded the moon&#39;s existance for centuries. Thanks to America&#39;s Space Program and the Apollo missions landing on the lunar surface, the entire world is closer to the heavens, and understanding the history of Earth.
<P>
This video reviews the breakthroughs lunar soil samples have rvealed. Rocks from the beginning of our solar system are providing greater clues to Earth&#39s age and origin. As we get new looks at the moon.
