<!--Volume 10-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v10.jpg">

<A NAME="v10"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>In the Mountains of the Moon</B></FONT></A>
<P>
<B>Awards</B><BR>
<I>Golden Eagle, Council on International Nontheatrical Events (CINE), 1972
<P>
Chris Award, 20th Annual Columbus Film Festival, 1972</I>
<P>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Charlie Duke
<P>
After man walked on the moon, more questions had to be answered. The samples brought home only opened new ideas into the origin of the moon, and the solar system.
<P>
Apollo 15 was the first of three missions sent to get a good look at the moon. This video shows you such exciting features as the standup spacewalk, traversing lunar soil via thr lunar rover, the launching of a subsatellite, and more. This award winning video is anouther must see in the history of America&#39;s Space Program.
