<!--Volume 13-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v13.jpg">

<A NAME="v13"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>On The Shoulders of Giants</B></FONT></A>
<P>
<B>Awards</B><BR>
<I>Chris Bronze Plaque Award, 21st Annual Columbus Film Festival, 1983
<P>
Trophy of the Italian Department of Defense, 1st International Review of Cinema and TV Films on Flight, Milan, Italy, 1974
<P>
Special Prize, 11th International Review of Technical, Scientific and Educational Films, Pardubice, Czechoslovakia, 1973
</I>
<P>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Rusty Schweickart
<P>
December 6, 1972, marked the end of an era. The Apollo era. As the program would take its final mission to the moon, it was the closing of a chapter, but still, just the beginning.
<P>
Float through space on Apollo 17 and enjoy heavenly views of Earth. Witness the gray and dusty surface of the moon as the astronauts work in this new world.
<P>
Celebrate with the crew and support team after capsule recovery, as you gain new understanding into the significant role the Apollo program played in the future of Skylab, the Space Shuttle and the first Russian-American joint space adventure: the Apollo-Soyuz linkup. This award-winning film is a must for any collector.
<P>
<P>
