<!--Volume 15-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg">

<A NAME="v15"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Skylab: The First Forty Days</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
30 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Pete Conrad
<P>
On the unmanned launch of Skylab 1, mission-threatening problems arose. Scientists had determined excessive heating of the space station was due to the loss of a meteoroid shield and the low power supply was due to ineffective solar panel deployment. Skylab 2 would have to be a repair mission if this program was to survive.
<P>
Without the ability to see what exactly had deterred the solar panels, astronauts had to perform deep-water executions to practice the repair. Before a single biomedical or scientific experiment would be undertaken, Skylab had to be fixed. Thanks to careful plans and training, the first 40 days of Skylab were a success.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="38" SRC="art/film.gif">Skylab: The First Forty Days, QuickTime sample available soon.
<BR>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio sample available soon.

