<HR>
<!--Volume 16-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg">

<A NAME="v16"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Skylab: The Second Manned Mission</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
45 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Rusty Schweickart
<P>
Skylab 2 would turn into a repair mission making way for Skylab 3's exciting scientific discoveries.
<P>
Human and animal reactions to zero gravity were studied using live minnows and spiders, and numerous physiological studies on the astronauts. Plus, an Apollo telescope mount recorded never before seen shots of the Sun.
<P>
Skylab provided greater information about our own planet's pollution, crop diseases, erosion and land use. It was a triumph of human intelligence. And a gateway to more.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Skylab: The Second Manned Mission,  QuickTime sample available soon.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio sample available soon.
