<!--Volume 17-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg">

<A NAME="v17"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Four Rooms, Earth View</B></FONT></A>
<P>
<B>Awards</B><BR>
<I>Silver Medal, International Film and TV Festival, New York, 1975
<P>
Golden Eagle, Council on International Nontheatrical Events (CINE), 1975
</I>
<P>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Pete Conrad
<P>
Skylab was a bold step towards the colonization of space. Experiments in zero gravity, solar observations and environmental resources were the focus of the 171 days in the orbiting laboratory. The findings and photos were so revolutionary, new confidence was instilled in America's space program.
<P>
E.G. Marshall hosts this dynamic video displaying what life may be in the future; fours rooms with an Earth view.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Four Rooms, Earth View,  QuickTime sample available soon.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
