<!--Volume 18-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v18.jpg">

<A NAME="v18"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Who&#39;s Out There</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut <A HREF="walt.htm">Walt Cunningham</A>
<P>
Orson Welles hosts this award winning production sure to make you think. Listen as he explains scientist's discovery of new galaxies in the universe, and the presence of life-forming elements in outer space. 
<P>
Watch a meeting of the great scientific minds as they conclude life is probably sustained in another galaxy, or on another planet. You'll see evidence Mars has active volcanoes, and what appears to be stream-cut relief. But the most astounding fact is, this film isn't fiction. It's the first steps in finding who's out there.
<P>
<A HREF="video/v18.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Who&#39;s Out There</A> - 4.1 MB QuickTime sample from the video
<P>
