<!--Volume 19-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg">

<A NAME="v19"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Mission of Apollo-Soyuz</B></FONT></A>
<P>
<B>Awards</B><BR>
<I>Golden Eagle, Council on International Nontheatrical Events (CINE), 1975.
</I>
<P>

35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Bob Overmyer
<P>
In 1972, America and Russia replaced political opposition with cooperation, signing the  Soviet-American Space Agreement. The Apollo-Soyuz mission would set precedent for sharing technologies. And after three years spent learning of each other's cultures and countries, the two spaceships left different ends of the earth to meet 140 miles above Portugal in the first phase of joint-outer-space explorations. Watch the story of this epic achievement and learn of future plans for even greater triumphs.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Mission of Apollo-Soyuz QuickTime sample available soon.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio sample available soon.
