<!--Volume 20-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v20.jpg">

<A NAME="v20"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>The Universe</B></FONT></A>
<P>
Awards<BR>
<I>Best Documentary - Short Subject Category in 49th Annual Awards Competition of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.
<P>
Bronze Medal - Council on International Nontheatrical Events (CINE), 1976.
<P>
Gold Camera Award - Best of Festival, United States Industrial Film Festival, 1977
</I>
<P>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Rusty Schweickart<BR>
Narrated by William Shatner
<P>
The drama and excitement unfolds as you discover the very nature of our planet, and the possibility of extraterrestrial life. Stars, planets, plants and humans are all made of the same elements. This film discusses the climate needed for these elements to evolve, and the likelihood this climate exists elsewhere in space.
<P>
Watch this award winning production and explore your own ideas of religion, philosophy, and alien life, as you explore "The Universe." 
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="video/v20.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">The Universe</A> - 3.6 MB QuickTime sample from the video
