<!--Volume 23-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v23.jpg">

<A NAME="v23"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>New Look at the Old Moon</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Pete Conrad
<P>
You&#39;ll see the moon like never before as this video brings you closer to the lunar surface.  NASA gives you an exciting review of the Apollo space findings and what they&#39;ve taught us about the planetary lifecycle, the moon&#39;s elemental  composition, and more.  Scientists have plans for the future use of the moon&#39;s vast supply of metals, and strategic position, great for further space exploration.  Watch this video and learn about the great eras of lunar history, as  you get a new look at the old moon.
<P>
<A HREF="video/v23.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">New Look at the Old Moon</A> - 6.2 MB QuickTime sample from the video
