<!--Volume 24-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/blank.jpg">

<A NAME="v24"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Space Shuttles</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Bob Overmyer
<P>
No spacecraft had ever taken its maiden voyage with astronauts aboard. But this was no ordinary mission. This was the first reusable, fixed-wing spacecraft to go into orbit. Millions witnessed the liftoff and landing firsthand and through television, and now you'll witness the entire mission.
<P>
Exciting photos and video animate this new decade of space exploration. And the dawning of a new era. The Space Shuttle era, a remarkable achievement, in space.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Space Shuttles  QuickTime sample available soon.
<P>
<IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio sample available soon.
<P>
