<!--Volume 25-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v25.jpg">

<A NAME="v25"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Opening New Frontiers</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
35 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Bob Overmyer
<P>
America's space program has accomplished much, but utilizing what we know costs money. So NASA developed the Space Shuttles to be the first reusable spacecrafts, designed to be an economical means to commercial and scientific achievements in space. Watch this documentary on the Orbital Flight Test Program and learn how thorough the planning and pretesting of shuttle equipment must be. No scientist can fully predict what will happen in space, when you're opening new frontiers.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="video/v25.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Opening New Frontiers</A> - 4.7 MB QuickTime sample from the video
<P>
<A HREF="v25.ram"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
