<!--Volume 27-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v27.jpg">

<A NAME="v27"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>NASA The 25th Year</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
55 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Alan Shepard
<P>
This is the complete chronicle of NASA's history, from the Explorer 1 in 1958, to the present Space Shuttle and Pioneer missions probing deeper into our solar system, and beyond. This video is a must for collectors, and is a sure delight to all who've ever wanted to learn more about America's Space Program, the greatest one on Earth.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="video/v27.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">NASA The 25th Year</A> - 6.1 MB QuickTime sample from the video
