<!--Volume 28-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v28.jpg">

<A NAME="v28"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Toys in Space</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
30 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Rusty Schweickart
<P>
If you've ever tried a yo-yo or paddle ball, you know it's not so easy. But think about trying to control these things in zero gravity. This film shows the Columbia crew attempt many of these games in space.
<P>
You'll hear their personal explanations of every detail of the mission, from liftoff to landing. Witness exciting medical experiments and watch the fun of weightlessness as the Columbia crew completes another successful orbit.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF="video/v28.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Toys in Space</A> - 3.6 MB QuickTime sample from the video
<P>
<A HREF="v28.ram"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
Audio</A> by astronaut Rusty Schweickart introducing <I>Toys in Space</I>.
