<HR>
<!--Volume 29-->
<P>
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="131" SRC="art/v29.jpg">

<A NAME="v29"><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Challenger Investigation/Return to Space</B></FONT></A>
<BR>
70 minutes<BR>
Introduced by Astronaut Rick Hauck
<P>
This is a special look at the seven Americans who gave their lives in the Challenger disaster. NASA had taken every precaution, as always, to ensure safety and confidence. It wasn't until the Shuttle had inched up from the launch pad that the mystery started to unfold. 
<P>
You'll see the facts and findings behind the investigation. And a technical explanation of what went wrong. The lesson will live forever in the future of America's space program. And so will the memory of the seven astronauts who boarded the Challenger for the last time.
<P>
America returned to space victoriously and courageously with the next shuttle, Discovery, commanded by Rick Hauck. Rick and his crew salute their Challenger colleagues in a moving memorium in outer space.
<P>

<A HREF="video/v29.qt"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="39" HEIGHT="34" SRC="art/film.gif">Challenger Investigation/Return to Space</A> - 4.4 MB QuickTime sample from the video
<P>
<A HREF="v29.ram"><IMG BORDER="0" ALIGN="middle" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="25" SRC="art/ra.gif">
