<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 19, 1996</b>
<dl>

<dt>01:53 pm
<dd>
Launch


<dt>02:36 pm
<dd>
OMS-2


<dt>03:18 pm
<dd>
PLBD opening


<dt>04:23 pm
<dd>
Jernigan powers up Columbia's robot arm; Musgrave activates and deploys the KU-band communications antenna


<dt>04:33 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin a checkout of the robot arm


<dt>04:38 pm
<dd>
Musgrave begins to activate Wake Shield Facility systems


<dt>05:18 pm
<dd>
Jernigan uses the robot arm to grapple the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite for systems activation


<dt>05:33 pm
<dd>
Jernigan begins to power up the ORFEUS-SPAS systems; Rominger activates the Extended Duration Orbiter pallet in the cargo bay to provide additional power for Columbia during the flight


<dt>05:53 pm
<dd>
Jones and Musgrave begin to activate laser range devices and other rendezvous tools prior to the ORFEUS-SPAS deployment


<dt>06:23 pm
<dd>
Jones configures on-board laptop computers for future Orbiter Space Vision System experiment work


<dt>07:38 pm
<dd>
Jernigan unberths the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>08:03 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger maneuver Columbia to the ORFEUS-SPAS deploy attitude


<dt>08:53 pm
<dd>
JERNIGAN AND JONES DEPLOY THE ORFEUS-SPAS SATELLITE FOR TWO WEEKS OF FREE-FLYING ASTRONOMY RESEARCH


<dt>08:54 pm
<dd>
Cockrell fires jets to begin seperating from the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>09:27 pm
<dd>
Cockrell fires jets to increase the seperation rate between Columbia and the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>09:38 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones power down the robot arm


<dt>10:14 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct a rendezvous burn to place Columbia in position to retrieve ORFEUS-SPAS two weeks from now


<dt>11:28 pm
<dd>
Private medical conference</dl>

<p><b>November 20, 1996</b>
<dl>

<dt>12:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins
</dl>







