<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; STS-80</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 21, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>09:53 am
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>12:53 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave begin to prepare Columbia's airlock for EVA operations later in the flight


<dt>01:20 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another ORFEUS-SPAS rendezvous burn to maintain a constant distance from the satellite


<dt>01:28 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave checkout the two prime spacesuits to be worn by Jernigan and Jones during their two spacewalks


<dt>02:53 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave checkout the spacesuit glove heaters


<dt>04:08 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave checkout the backup spacesuit which would be needed in a contingency for spacewalking assistance


<dt>05:03 pm
<dd>
Musgrave exercises


<dt>05:43 pm
<dd>
PAO Opportunity with Cockrell and Rominger


<dt>06:53 pm
<dd>
Rominger collects more data from the VIEW-CAPL experiment; Jones and Musgrave begin Wake Shield Facility predeployment preparations; Cockrell turns off non-essential backup systems to conserve power aboard Columbia


<dt>08:03 pm
<dd>
Cockrell monitors a waste water dump; Jernigan exercises


<dt>08:53 pm
<dd>
Jones exercises


<dt>09:23 pm
<dd>
Jernigan collects data from the VIEW-CAPL experiment


<dt>10:25 pm
<dd>
Rominger exercises; Crew Choice TV with Jones


<dt>10:53 pm
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


<dt>11:23 pm
<dd>
Musgrave checks on the rodents which are part of the PARE-NIH experiment</dl>

<p><b>November 22, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>01:33 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to maintain distance with the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>01:38 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>02:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins</dl>






