</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 23, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>11:53 am
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>02:30 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to maintain distaces with the WSF and the ORFEUS-SPAS


<dt>03:08 pm
<dd>
Jernigan resumes work with the VIEW-CAPL experiment; Crew Choice TV with Jones


<dt>03:48 pm
<dd>
Jones provides a videotape replay of the WSF deployment


<dt>04:38 pm
<dd>
Rominger exercises


<dt>05:08 pm
<dd>
Musgrave exercises


<dt>05:38 pm
<dd>
PAO Opportunity with Cockrell, Jernigan and Jones


<dt>06:03 pm
<dd>
Rominger works with the VIEW-CAPL experiment


<dt>06:23 pm
<dd>
Cockrell cleans orbiter filters


<dt>06:53 pm
<dd>
Jernigan exercises


<dt>08:53 pm
<dd>
Rominger continues work with the VIEW-CAPL eperiment


<dt>10:13 pm
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


<dt>11:13 pm
<dd>
Jernigan works with the VIEW-CAPL experiment</dl>

<p><b>November 24, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>11/24/96 12:08 am
<dd>
Crew Choice TV with Rominger


<dt>11/24/96 12:53 am
<dd>
Jones exercises


<dt>11/24/96 01:11 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to keep with the WSF and ORFEUS-SPAS satellites


<dt>11/24/96 01:23 am
<dd>
Cockrell checks on the rodents which are part of the PARE-NIH experiment


<dt>11/24/96 02:53 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>11/24/96 04:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins</dl>






