<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; STS-80</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 25, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>01:53 pm
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>03:23 pm
<dd>
Cockrell powers up backup systems for the WSF rendezvous


<dt>05:03 pm
<dd>
Jones exercises


<dt>05:47 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct a rendezvous burn to close in on the WSF


<dt>06:08 pm
<dd>
Jernigan powers up the robot arm


<dt>06:34 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct a height adjustment maneuver to refine Columbia's path to the WSF


<dt>07:54 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct a course correction maneuver to edge closer to the WSF


<dt>08:51 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct the Terminal Initiation (TI) burn to place Columbia on an intercepting path to the WSF


<dt>11:10 pm
<dd>
JONES GRAPPLES THE WAKE SHIELD FACILITY TO END ITS THREE-DAY FREE FLIGHT; Jernigan powers up the Orbiter Space Vision System hardware


<dt>11:38 pm
<dd>
Jones and Jernigan berth the Wake Shield Facility back on its platform in the cargo bay


<dt>11:53 pm
<dd>
Jones powers down the robot arm and Jernigan powers down the Orbiter Space Vision System hardware</dl>

<b>November 26, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>12:23 am
<dd>
Cockrell conducts a check of the rodents in the PARE-NIH experiment; Rominger exercises; Jones monitors a waste water dump


<dt>12:53 am
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


<dt>01:23 am
<dd>
Musgrave exercises


<dt>01:53 am
<dd>
Jernigan exercises


<dt>02:08 am
<dd>
Jones provides a videotape replay of the WSF retrieval


<dt>02:48 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to maintain distance from the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>04:20 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct yet another ORFEUS-SPAS rendezvous burn


<dt>04:23 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>05:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins</dl>






