<HTML>
<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; STS-80</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 26, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>01:53 pm
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>04:33 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to refine the Shuttle's path to the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>04:53 pm
<dd>
Cockrell deactivates the Regenerative Carbon Dioxide Removal System in preparation for WSF attached science operations; Rominger exercises


<dt>05:23 pm
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


<dt>05:28 pm
<dd>
Jones powers up the robot arm


<dt>05:48 pm
<dd>
Jones grapples the Wake Shield Facility and unberths it with Jernigan's help for several hours of attached science operations


<dt>06:23 pm
<dd>
Rominger resumes VIEW-CAPL experiment work


<dt>07:38 pm
<dd>
Jernigan exercises; Cockrell cleans orbiter filters


<dt>08:38 pm
<dd>
Rominger continues work with the VIEW-CAPL experiment; Jones and Jernigan conduct Orbiter Space Vision System experiments with the WSF at the end of the robot arm


<dt>09:08 pm
<dd>
Cockrell reactivates the Regenerative Carbon Dioxide scrubbing system to resume the cleaning of the Shuttle's air supply


<dt>09:23 pm
<dd>
Musgrave exercises


<dt>09:38 pm
<dd>
Jones berths the Wake Shield Facility back on its platform in the cargo bay for the final time; Jernigan powers down the Orbiter Space Vision System


<dt>10:03 pm
<dd>
Jones powers down the robot arm


<dt>11:23 pm
<dd>
Cockrell powers down non-essential backup equipment to conserve electricity; Jernigan resumes work with the VIEW-CAPL experiment</dl>

<p><b>November 27, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>12:23 am
<dd>
Jones exercises


<dt>01:33 am
<dd>
PAO Opportunity with Cockrell, Rominger and Musgrave


<dt>02:03 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger depress Columbia's cabin pressure from 14.7 psi to 10.2 psi in preparation for future spacewalk activity


<dt>02:14 am
<dd>
Crew Choice TV with Musgrave


<dt>02:53 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>03:08 am
<dd>
Private family conference for Jones and Musgrave; Cockrell checks on the rodents in the PARE-NIH experiment; Rominger stows the VIEW-CAPL experiment


<dt>04:46 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to stay within striking distance of the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>06:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins</dl>






