	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; STS-80</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 28, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>02:53 pm
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>05:25 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn for the retrieval of the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>05:53 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave begin EVA prep in the middeck area; Rominger exercises


<dt>06:33 pm
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


<dt>07:03 pm
<dd>
Rominger powers up the robot arm for use during the spacewalk by Jernigan and Jones


<dt>07:23 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin 45 minutes of prebreathing pure oxygen to cleanse the nitrogen from their bloodstreams prior to beginning their spacewalk


<dt>08:13 pm
<dd>
Columbia's airlock is depressurized


<dt>08:23 pm
<dd>
JERNIGAN AND JONES FLOAT OUT INTO COLUMBIA'S CARGO BAY TO BEGIN THEIR FIRST SPACEWALK


<dt>08:43 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin to setup a crane in the payload bay to haul large components back and forth in a test of International Space Station (ISS) assembly tasks


<dt>09:13 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones test the crane


<dt>09:33 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin to move large Orbital Replacement Units (ORU's) around the cargo bay through the use of the crane device

<p><b>November 29, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>12:28 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin to move small ORU's around the cargo bay through the use of the crane device


<dt>12:53 am
<dd>
With the spacewalk in progress, Cockrell checks on the rodents in the PARE-NIH experiment


<dt>01:13 am
<dd>
Jernigan tests an ISS power tool while Jones evaluates improved foot restraints and other spacewalking aids


<dt>01:43 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin to stow the crane device


<dt>02:13 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones stow their tools


<dt>02:53 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones float back into the airlock to complete EVA # 1; Rominger powers down the robot arm


<dt>03:03 am
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave resupply spacesuit water systems and recharge spacesuit batteries for EVA # 2


<dt>04:06 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to keep pace with the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>06:23 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>07:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins
</DL>






