<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>November 30, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>03:53 pm
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>06:17 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn for the retrieval of the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>06:23 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave begin EVA preparations in the middeck area; Rominger exercises


<dt>06:58 pm
<dd>
Cockrell monitors a waste water dump


<dt>07:33 pm
<dd>
Rominger powers up the robot arm for use during the spacewalk by Jernigan and Jones


<dt>07:53 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin a 45-minute prebreathe of pure oxygen in the airlock to cleanse nitrogen from their bloodstreams


<dt>08:53 pm
<dd>
JERNIGAN AND JONES FLOAT BACK INTO COLUMBIA'S CARGO BAY TO BEGIN EVA # 2


<dt>09:08 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones setup tools and portable work platforms in the cargo bay


<dt>10:23 pm
<dd>
Jernigan hauls large Orbital Rpelacement Unit boxes around the cargo bay while affixed to a Portable Work Platform; Jones evaluates different types of restraint tethers; Cockrell repressurizes Columbia's cabin from 10.2 psi to 14.7 psi


<dt>10:53 pm
<dd>
Cockrell powers up backup systems for the rest of the flight


<dt>11:38 pm
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones swap places to continue their tool and hardware evaluations</dl>

<p><b>December 1, 1996</b><dl>
12:53 am
<dd>
Cockrell checks on the rodents in the PARE-NIH experiment


01:13 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones evaluate mass handling capability while in Portable Work Platforms at the end of the robot arm


01:43 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones begin tool stowage and Portable Work Platform stowage


01:53 am
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


02:53 am
<dd>
Cockrell cleans orbiter filters


03:23 am
<dd>
Jernigan and Jones float back into Columbia's airlock to complete EVA # 2; Rominger powers down the robot arm


03:33 am
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave refill water supplies in the spacesuits and recharge spacesuit batteries


04:58 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to refine Columbia's path to the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


06:18 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


07:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins ( 9 hours )</dl>






