<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; STS-80</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>December 1, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>04:53 pm
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>06:43 pm
<dd>
Jones exercises


<dt>07:53 pm
<dd>
Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave begin 4 hours of off-duty time


<dt>08:15 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to catch up to the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>08:18 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger begin their off-duty period</dl>

<p><b>December 2, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>12:53 am
<dd>
Cockrell checks the rodents in the PARE-NIH experiment; Jernigan, Jones and Musgrave conduct post-EVA entry preparation for spacesuits and tools


<dt>01:33 am
<dd>
Jernigan powers up the robot arm and the Orbiter Space Vision System hardware and, along with Jones, begins an OSVS survey run


<dt>01:53 am
<dd>
Musgrave begins to transfer data on the performance of the EVA tools to disc on a laptop computer; Rominger exercises


<dt>02:23 am
<dd>
Cockrell exercises


<dt>02:53 am
<dd>
Jernigan powers down the robot arm and joins Jones fill out a questionnaire about EVA # 2; Musgrave exercises


<dt>03:23 am
<dd>
Cockrell uses the Portable In-Flight Landing Operations Trainer (PILOT) to sharpen his landing skills on the laptop computer simulator


<dt>03:43 am
<dd>
PAO Opportunity with Jernigan and Jones


<dt>03:53 am
<dd>
Rominger takes a turn sharpening his landing skills with the PILOT laptop trainer; Jernigan exercises; Jones and Musgrave stow EVA tools


<dt>05:32 am
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger conduct another rendezvous burn to catch up to the ORFEUS-SPAS satellite


<dt>06:38 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>06:53 am
<dd>
Private family conferences for Cockrell, Rominger and Jernigan


<dt>07:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins</dl>






