<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; STS-80</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="189" HEIGHT="190" SRC="art/80patch.gif"ALT="STS-80 Patch">
<BR>
<P>

<H1>Shuttle Mission STS-80</H1><BR>

<P>
<A HREF="80time.htm">Back to Mission Timeline</A>
<BR CLEAR="all">
<b>December 3, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>04:53 pm
<dd>
Crew wakeup


<dt>05:13 pm
<dd>
Jones monitors a waste water dump


<dt>07:58 pm
<dd>
CREW NEWS CONFERENCE WITH ALL CREWMEMBERS


<dt>08:43 pm
<dd>
Cockrell and Rominger pulse Columbia's vernier reaction control system jets in an exercise to gather data on the use of this method to reboost the Hubble Space Telescope following its second servicing in February


<dt>09:48 pm
<dd>
Musgrave stows Columbia's KU-band communications antenna


<dt>09:53 pm
<dd>
Cockrell exercises; Rominger practices landings with the PILOT laptop computer trainer; Musgrave deactivates the Space Experiment Module


<dt>10:23 pm
<dd>
Jones takes a turn practicing landings on the PILOT laptop computer trainer


<dt>10:23 pm
<dd>
Rominger exercises


<dt>10:33 pm
<dd>
Jernigan stows the Orbiter Space Vision System for the final time


<dt>10:53 pm
<dd>
Cockrell takes a turn practicing landings on the PILOT laptop computer trainer</dl>

<p><b>December 4, 1996</b><dl>
<dt>12:23 am
<dd>
Cockrell, Rominger and Jones begin the checkout of Columbia's flight control systems in a routine pre-landing health test; Jernigan and Musgrave begin to stow Columbia's cabin


<dt>01:18 am
<dd>
Jernigan exercises


<dt>01:33 am
<dd>
Cockrell, Rominger and Jones hot-fire Columbia's reaction control system jets to insure that they are ready to support entry and landing


<dt>01:53 am
<dd>
Cockrell checks the rodents in the PARE-NIH experiment; Jones exercises


<dt>02:23 am
<dd>
Cockrell cleans orbiter filters; Musgrave exercises; cabin stow continues


<dt>04:13 am
<dd>
Rominger and Jernigan stow the bicycle ergometer


<dt>04:43 am
<dd>
Musgrave stows Columbia's KU-band communications antenna


<dt>05:48 am
<dd>
Rominger conducts routine L-1 communications checks with ground stations at Edwards Air Force Base, CA and the Merritt Island Tracking Station near the Kennedy Space Center


<dt>06:08 am
<dd>
Private medical conference


<dt>07:23 am
<dd>
A backup opportunity, if required, for L-1 communications checks with landing sites in California and Florida


<dt>07:53 am
<dd>
Crew sleep begins ( 9 1/2 hours )</dl>






