<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 2</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<b>September 16, 1996</b>
<dl>
<dt>04:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>07:34 p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt conduct a rendezvous burn to fine-tune Atlantis'
course to the Mir

<p>
<dt>07:54 p.m.
<dd>Wilcutt sets up the bicycle ergometer in the middeck; Apt and Walz
continue activating Spacehab systems; Akers cleans orbiter filters

<p>
<dt>08:24 p.m.
<dd>Readdy exercises; Wilcutt begins to load water into bags for eventual
transfer to the Mir; Apt sets up Spacehab module systems; Walz activates a
radiation monitoring device in Spacehab; Blaha collects Shuttle air samples
for study; Akers exercises

<p>
<dt>09:24 p.m.
<dd>Apt and Walz begin to setup the ARIS (Active Rack Isolation System)
experiment in the Spacehab designed to dampen vibrations on Space Station
experiments; Akers repacks transfer items earmarked for the Mir Space
Station

<p>
<dt>09:34 p.m.
<dd>Wilcutt exercises

<p>
<dt>10:24 p.m.
<dd>Readdy exercises

<p>
<dt>10:54 p.m.
<dd>Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>11:09 p.m.
<dd>Blaha photographs Shuttle surface characteristics; Akers begins to setup
IMAX camera gear
</dl>

<p><b>September 17, 1996</b>
<dl>
<dt>12:54 a.m.
<dd>Apt and Walz continue setting up the ARIS experiment

<p>
<dt>01:08 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt conduct another rendezvous burn to refine Atlantis'
path to the Mir

<p>
<dt>01:44 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Blaha setup the VHF radio system and the SAREX ham radio
gear; Wilcutt and Akers mount the centerline camera in the Orbiter Docking
System

<p>
<dt>01:54 a.m.
<dd>Apt activates the Shuttle Acceleration Measurement system

<p>
<dt>02:09 a.m.
<dd>Akers checks out handheld laser devices for tomorrow's rendezvous;
Walz begins to test the ARIS system; Wilcutt checks out other rendezvous
tools

<p>
<dt>02:24 a.m.
<dd>Akers prepares rendezvous cameras

<p>
<dt>02:54 a.m.
<dd>Apt charges the Electronic Still Camera

<p>
<dt>04:39 a.m.
<dd>Walz configures GPS navigation devices for on-board computer use; Apt
prepares the Extreme Temperature furnace in the Spacehab for activation

<p>
<dt>05:24 a.m.
<dd>Apt conduct a test of the SAREX ham radio gear over Houston

<p>
<dt>06:03 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt conduct another rendezvous burn to tweak Atlantis'
path to the Mir

<p>
<dt>07:54 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>08:54 a.m.
<dd>Atlantis' crew sleep begins

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Mir 22 crew sleep begins (9 hours)
</dl>



