<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 3</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p><b>September 17, 1996</b>
<dl>

<p>
<dt>04:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>07:33 p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt execute another rendezvous burn to reach the Mir
Space Station; Akers cleans orbiter filters; Walz sets up and activates an
experiment (MGM) to analyze the effect of weightlessness on granular
materials

<p>
<dt>07:59 p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Blaha exercise

<p>
<dt>08:59 p.m.
<dd>Wilcutt exercises

<p>
<dt>09:34 p.m.
<dd>CREW CHOICE TV WITH WALZ CONDUCTING A TOUR OF THE SPACEHAB
MODULE

<p>
<dt>09:54 p.m.
<dd>Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>11:09 p.m.
<dd>U.S. PAO Opportunity with Readdy, Blaha and Akers</dl>
<p><b>September 18, 1996</b>
<dl>

<p>
<dt>01:29 a.m.
<dd>Apt conducts a SAREX contact with a school in Andover, Kansas

<p>
<dt>02:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz exercises

<p>
<dt>03:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz extends the outer ring of the Orbiter Docking System to verify its
health for tomorrow's docking with the Mir Space Station

<p>
<dt>03:44 a.m.
<dd>Walz conducts a SAREX contact with a school in Celina, Ohio

<p>
<dt>03:54 a.m.
<dd>Akers exercises

<p>
<dt>05:04 a.m.
<dd>Walz deactivates the GPS laptop computer experiments

<p>
<dt>06:35 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt conduct a rendezvous burn and height adjustment as
they close in on the Mir

<p>
<dt>07:29 a.m.
<dd>Blaha conducts a personal SAREX contact

<p>
<dt>07:54 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>08:54 a.m.
<dd>Atlantis' crew sleep begins (7 hours)

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Mir 22 crew sleep begins (6 hours)</dl>


