<HTML>
<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 4</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p><b>September 18, 1996</b>
<dl>


<p>
<dt>03:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>04:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis' astronauts enter their rendezvous checklist

<p>
<dt>06:01 p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt conduct another rendezvous burn to the Mir (NC 4)

<p>
<dt>06:54 p.m.
<dd>Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>06:59 p.m.
<dd>Apt and Blaha on Atlantis and Korzun on the Mir activate VHF radio
systems for communication during rendezvous and docking

<p>
<dt>07:33 p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt execute the Terminal Initiation (TI) rendezvous burn
to place Atlantis on an intercepting path to a point below the Mir

<p>
<dt>07:59 p.m.
<dd>Akers catches the first view of Mir out of Atlantis' overhead windows;
aboard Mir, Kaleri commands the station's solar arrays to an edge-on, or
"feathered" position for docking

<p>
<dt>08:53 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis arrives at a point about 1500 feet below the Mir along the
R-Bar, or radial vector to the Earth; Readdy, working from aft flight deck
controls, begins to fly Atlantis up the R-Bar toward Mir

<p>
<dt>09:35 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis begins about 11 minutes of stationkeeping 170 feet from the
Mir to enable flight controllers in Mission Control, Houston and Mission
Control, Korolev to assess their spacecraft's systems

<p>
<dt>09:46 p.m.
<dd>Flight Directors Paul Dye and Victor Blagov poll their flight teams to get
a "go" for the resumption of Atlantis' approach to the Mir; Readdy continues
toward the Mir

<p>
<dt>09:49 p.m.
<dd>Walz powers up Atlantis' docking mechanism

<p>
<dt>10:04 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis' approach is once again halted at 30 feet for about 6 minutes of
stationkeeping to enable U.S. and Russian flight controllers to make a final
assessment of spacecraft systems

<p>
<dt>10:10 p.m.
<dd>Readdy begins his final approach to the Mir

<p>
<dt>10:17 p.m.
<dd>ATLANTIS DOCKS TO THE MIR SPACE STATION FOR THE FOURTH TIME,
INITIATING THE CAPTURE AND LATCHING OF HOOKS BETWEEN THE ORBITER
DOCKING SYSTEM AND THE DOCKING MODULE DOCKING MECHANISM

<p>
<dt>10:37 p.m.
<dd>A hard mate between Atlantis and Mir is established as the linkup of
hooks and latches is completed between both spacecraft's docking
mechanisms

<p>
<dt>10:44 p.m.
<dd>Pressure and leak checks are conducted by both crews of the hatches
connecting the Orbiter Docking System to the Russian Docking Module

<p>
<dt>10:54 p.m.
<dd>Walz reenters the Spacehab to configure the module's systems for joint
scientific operations

<p>
<dt>11:39 p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt provide a videotape replay of Atlantis' docking to the
Mir</dl>

<p><b>September 19, 1996</b>
<dl>

<p>
<dt>12:39 a.m.
<dd>THE HATCHES ARE OPENED BETWEEN ATLANTIS AND MIR AND COMMANDERS
READDY AND KORZUN SHAKE HANDS TO BEGIN FIVE DAYS OF JOINT
OPERATIONS; A GIFT EXCHANGE AND WELCOMING CEREMONY IS CONDUCTED IN
THE MIR CORE MODULE

<p>
<dt>01:19 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt begins to transfer water from Atlantis to the Mir

<p>
<dt>02:39 a.m.
<dd>The nine astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a safety briefing on Mir
systems

<p>
<dt>03:14 a.m.
<dd>Readdy conducts a Shuttle safety briefing with Korzun and Kaleri

<p>
<dt>03:34 a.m.
<dd>Blaha unstows and begins to transfer his Soyuz seatliner to the Mir; Apt
and Kaleri move the crosshair docking target from the Mir to the Shuttle

<p>
<dt>03:54 a.m.
<dd>Blaha and Lucid transfer Blaha's Soyuz seatliner from Atlantis to the Mir
to mark Blaha officially joining the Mir crew and Lucid officially joining the
Shuttle crew

<p>
<dt>04:24 a.m.
<dd>Blaha and Korzun install Blaha's seatliner in the Soyuz capsule

<p>
<dt>05:04 a.m.
<dd>Readdy exercises

<p>
<dt>05:39 a.m.
<dd>Apt exercises

<p>
<dt>06:24 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt exercises aboard Atlantis; Lucid exercises on the Mir treadmill

<p>
<dt>06:54 a.m.
<dd>The two crews conduct a tagup with respective Mission Control Centers
to debrief officials on initial transfer activities and plans for tomorrow's
transfer work

<p>
<dt>09:24 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>09:39 a.m.
<dd>Lucid conducts a private family conference

<p>
<dt>10:54 a.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew sleep begins (10 hours)</dl>



<HR>


