	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 5</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p>September 19, 1996</p>
<dl>
<p>
<dt>08:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>10:54 p.m.
<dd>All nine astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a daily planning session
regarding transfer and flight plan activities

<p>
<dt>11:24 p.m.
<dd>Walz activates an experiment to study granular materials in
weightlessness; the Mir 22 crew conducts transfer work along with Akers
</dl>
<p>September 20, 1996
<dl>
<p>
<dt>12:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz exercises; Lucid and Blaha continue handover chores

<p>
<dt>01:24 a.m.
<dd>Apt and Walz remove a biotechnology sampling device from the Spacehab
and transfer it to the Mir's Priroda module for use by Blaha during his
mission

<p>
<dt>02:24 a.m.
<dd>Apt and Blaha turn off the biotechnology experiment in the Priroda
module; Akers and Lucid continue the transfer of cold stowage items; CREW
CHOICE TV WITH READDY AND WILCUTT

<p>
<dt>03:09 a.m.
<dd>Apt, Blaha and Kaleri setup the Biotechnology Engineering Development
Unit in Priroda; Akers and Lucid defrost a thermoelectric refrigerator aboard
the Mir

<p>
<dt>04:54 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt, Akers and Lucid continue Shuttle-Mir transfer work; Apt, Blaha
and Kaleri transfer a Commercial Generic Bioprocessing Apparatus to Priroda
for Blaha's use

<p>
<dt>05:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz begins to conduct a photographic survey of the Mir for engineering
documentation

<p>
<dt>06:14 a.m.
<dd>U.S. PAO Opportunity with Readdy, Wilcutt, Lucid, Blaha and Korzun in the
Mir Core Module

<p>
<dt>06:34 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt and Korzun continue transfer activities; Apt exercises; Lucid and
Blaha continue to handover responsibilities on the Mir; Walz and Kaleri
transfer the IMAX camera to the Spektr module in the Mir

<p>
<dt>07:39 a.m.
<dd>Akers exercises; The setup of the IMAX camera in the Spektr module is
completed

<p>
<dt>08:24 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt exercises; Lucid exercises on the Mir treadmill; Blaha hasa
private family conference

<p>
<dt>08:54 a.m.
<dd>The astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a daily tagup on transfer and
flight plan activities

<p>
<dt>10:09 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>10:24 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt conduct a private family conference

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew sleep begins </dl>



