	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 6</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p>September 20, 1996</p>
<dl>
<p>
<dt>08:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>09:54 p.m.
<dd>Korzun uses Mir attitude control jets to assume control of the
Shuttle-Mir complex

<p>
<dt>11:24 p.m.
<dd>Readdy reassumes control of the Shuttle-Mir complex orientation

<p>
<dt>11:54 p.m.
<dd>The astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a daily tagup on transfer and
flight plan activities
</dl>
<p>September 21, 1996
<dl>
<p>
<dt>12:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz sets up the granular materials experiment; Lucid exercises on the
Mir treadmill; Blaha begins biomedical tests as part of his four-month
protocol on the Mir

<p>
<dt>12:54 a.m.
<dd>With Apt monitoring the Active Rack Isolation Experiment in the
Spacehab, Readdy and Korzun conduct jet firings on the Shuttle and the Mir to
test the response of the system to isolate experiments from vibrations

<p>
<dt>01:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz helps Korzun and Kaleri transfer Russian Orlan spacesuits from the
Spacehab to the Mir for future use by cosmonaut spacewalkers; Blaha and
Lucid continue their handover activities

<p>
<dt>02:09 a.m.
<dd>Walz, Korzun and Kaleri stow the Orlan suits in the Mir; Apt conducts
photographic surveys of the Mir; Readdy exercises; Akers uses the IMAX
camera to capture scenes of Lucid and Blaha in the Spektr module; Korzun
exercises on the Mir treadmill

<p>
<dt>02:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz and Kaleri deactivate the electrical interference experiment in the
Mir

<p>
<dt>02:29 a.m.
<dd>Apt conducts a photographic survey of the Mir from the Shuttle flight
deck

<p>
<dt>03:24 a.m.
<dd>Akers shoots IMAX scenes of Readdy, Wilcutt and Korzun in the Spektr
module

<p>
<dt>03:49 a.m.
<dd>VIP Opportunity with ALL crewmembers in the Mir Core Module (if
necessary; will be deleted if no VIP call is requested)

<p>
<dt>04:24 a.m.
<dd>Apt and Lucid conduct a SAREX ham radio contact with a school in
Surrey, England

<p>
<dt>05:29 a.m.
<dd>Russian Media Opportunity with ALL crewmembers in the Mir Core Module
( will not be seen on NASA TV )

<p>
<dt>05:54 a.m.
<dd>Apt, Blaha and Kaleri transfer the Single Thermal Enclosure
biotechnology system from the Shuttle to the Mir

<p>
<dt>05:59 a.m.
<dd>Akers exercises

<p>
<dt>07:24 a.m.
<dd>Walz photographs the Mir from Spacehab overhead windows; Akers cleans
orbiter filters; Lucid and Blaha continue their handover; Kaleri exercises on
the Mir treadmill

<p>
<dt>07:54 a.m.
<dd>Akers and Korzun relocate the IMAX camera in the Priroda module

<p>
<dt>08:24 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt exercise; Lucid exercises on the Mir treadmill

<p>
<dt>08:29 a.m.
<dd>CREW CHOICE TV WITH WALZ

<p>
<dt>09:24 a.m.
<dd>The astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a daily tagup on transfer and
flight plan activities

<p>
<dt>10:24 a.m.
<dd>Lucid conducts a private family conference

<p>
<dt>10:54 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>11:09 a.m.
<dd>Apt conducts a private family conference

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew sleep begins</dl>



