<HTML>
<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 8</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p>September 22, 1996</p>
<dl>
<p>
<dt>08:54p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>10:59p.m.
<dd>Readdy and Korzun conduct a primary reaction control system jet firing
to test the structural response and stability of the Mir

<p>
<dt>11:54p.m.
<dd>The astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a daily tagup on transfer and
flight plan activities
</dl>
<p>September 23, 1996
<dl>
<p>
<dt>12:24 a.m.
<dd>Lucid exercises on the Mir treadmill; Blaha collects water from the
Shuttle's tanks as Kaleri photographs the operation in progress

<p>
<dt>12:44 a.m.
<dd>Akers and Walz take turns shooting scenes of activity in the Mir Core
Module

<p>
<dt>02:44 a.m.
<dd>JOINT U.S.-RUSSIAN CREW NEWS CONFERENCE WITH ALL CREWMEMBERS IN
THE MIR CORE MODULE

<p>
<dt>03:39 a.m.
<dd>The astronauts and cosmonauts conduct a final tagup to take inventory
on all transfer items which have moved between the Shuttle and the Mir

<p>
<dt>04:44 a.m.
<dd>THE ASTRONAUTS AND COSMONAUTS CONDUCT A FAREWELL CEREMONY
AND FINAL GIFT EXCHANGE IN THE MIR CORE MODULE

<p>
<dt>05:59 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt and Korzun transfer Russian food items to the Mir contained in
ARIS racks in the Spacehab; Akers returns the IMAX camera from the Mir to
the Shuttle; Lucid and Blaha complete handover activities

<p>
<dt>06:44 a.m.
<dd>The astronauts and cosmonauts conduct final transfers prior to hatch
closure

<p>
<dt>07:04 a.m.
<dd>Akers and Kaleri remove the air duct running between the Shuttle and the
Mir prior to hatch closure

<p>
<dt>07:14 a.m.
<dd>AFTER FINAL FAREWELLS, READDY AND KORZUN CLOSE THE HATCHES
BETWEEN ATLANTIS AND MIR, LEAVING BLAHA BEHIND TO BEGIN HIS 4 1/2
MONTH RESEARCH MISSION; Lucid exercises

<p>
<dt>07:34 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Akers mount the centerline camera in the Orbiter Docking
System for tomorrow's undocking

<p>
<dt>08:04 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt sets up rendezvous tools for tomorrow's undocking; Akers begins
to stow transfer items from the Mir; Korzun exercises on the Mir treadmill;
Kaleri exercises on the Mir ergometer

<p>
<dt>08:34 a.m.
<dd>Readdy exercises; Walz conducts final photographic surveys of the Mir
out of the Shuttle's windows

<p>
<dt>09:24 a.m.
<dd>Atlantis' astronauts conduct a daily tagup of flight plan activities

<p>
<dt>10:34 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>10:44 a.m.
<dd>Walz conducts a private family conference

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew sleep begins (6 hours)</dl>


