<HTML>
<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 9</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p>September 23, 1996</p>
<dl>
<p>
<dt>06:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis and Mir 22 crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>07:29 p.m.
<dd>Korzun and Kaleri maneuver the Mir-Shuttle complex into the undocking
attitude; Lucid and Walz setup the IMAX camera to record undocking

<p>
<dt>08:31 p.m.
<dd>READDY AND WILCUTT COMMAND DOCKING HOOKS AND LATCHES TO OPEN
AND ATLANTIS GENTLY UNDOCKS FROM THE MIR TO LEAVE BLAHA BEHIND FOR
FOUR MONTHS OF SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH

<p>
<dt>08:41 p.m.
<dd>At a distance of 150 feet apart from one another, the Mir assumes
attitude control after being in indicator mode and the Shuttle prepares to
begin its flyaround

<p>
<dt>08:51 p.m.
<dd>Some 400 feet below Mir, Wilcutt initiates a tail forward flyaround of
the Mir

<p>
<dt>08:56 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis reaches a point 400 feet in front of the Mir on the +V-Bar

<p>
<dt>09:11 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis reaches a point 400 feet above Mir along the -R-Bar

<p>
<dt>09:26 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis reaches a point 400 feet behind the Mir along the -V-Bar

<p>
<dt>09:36 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis reaches a point 400 feet below the Mir along the +R-Bar

<p>
<dt>09:46 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crosses the +V-Bar again 400 feet in front of Mir

<p>
<dt>09:56 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crosses the -R-Bar again 400 feet above the Mir

<p>
<dt>10:06 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crosses the -V-Bar again 400 feet behind the Mir

<p>
<dt>10:16 p.m.
<dd>400 FEET BELOW THE MIR, WILCUTT FIRES ATLANTIS' JETS ONE MORE TIME
IN A FINAL SEPERATION BURN TO PART FROM THE RUSSIAN SPACE STATION
UNTIL THE SHUTTLE RETURNS DURING STS-81 IN JANUARY

<p>
<dt>11:09 p.m.
<dd>Walz exercises

<p>
<dt>11:54 p.m.
<dd>Apt exercises; Wilcutt cleans orbiter filters; Akers and Walz shoot IMAX
scenes aboard the Shuttle; Lucid conducts a personal SAREX ham radio
contact
</dl>
<p>September 24, 1996
<dl>
<p>
<dt>12:54 a.m.
<dd>Readdy exercises

<p>
<dt>01:24 a.m.
<dd>Lucid exercises

<p>
<dt>01:54 a.m.
<dd>Walz deactivates the GPS laptop computer gear

<p>
<dt>02:24 a.m.
<dd>U.S. PAO Opportunity with ALL crewmembers

<p>
<dt>02:44 a.m.
<dd>Atlantis' astronauts begin about 4 1/2 hours of off-duty time to relax

<p>
<dt>07:39 a.m.
<dd>Lucid exercises

<p>
<dt>08:54 a.m.
<dd>Readdy and Wilcutt exercise; Walz activates an experiment to download
data collected on the electric field potential around the Mir

<p>
<dt>10:34 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis' crew sleep begins ( 9 hours )</dl>



