<HEAD>
	<TITLE>SPACEZONE &#149; SPACE NEWS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--Copyrigh© 1996 Warner International Communications Group, Inc. All Rights Reserved.-->
<P><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#1113AB" VLINK="#B40FB"
ALINK="#F0051" >
<BODY>

<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="395" HEIGHT="119" SRC="art/szlogo.gif" ALT="SpaceZone">
<BR CLEAR="all">
<IMG ALIGN="left" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="198" SRC="art/patch.gif"ALT="STS-79 Patch">
<BR>
<P>
<H1>Astronaut Exchange
<BR>Shuttle Mission STS-79</H1>
<BR>

 <H2><A HREF="time.htm">Mission Timeline</A></H2>
 <H2>Flight Day 10</H2>
 
 <BR CLEAR="all">
 
<p>September 24, 1996
<dl>
<p>
<dt>09:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis crew wakeup

<p>
<dt>11:44 p.m.
<dd>Walz deactivates the Mir Electric Fields experiment which was used to
collect data on electrical interference around the Russian Space Station
</dl>
<p>September 25, 1996
<dl>
<p>
<dt>12:04 a.m.
<dd>Walz exercises

<p>
<dt>12:34 a.m.
<dd>Readdy, Wilcutt and Akers pulse Atlantis' vernier jets in another reboost
test to collect data for the Hubble Space Telescope servicing mission in
February

<p>
<dt>01:34 a.m.
<dd>The astronauts spend a few minutes reviewing entry and landing
procedures in a deorbit briefing

<p>
<dt>02:04 a.m.
<dd>Readdy, Wilcutt and Akers conduct a test of Atlantis' flight control
systems to insure their health for tomorrow's landing; Apt and Walz stow
the ARIS experiment in the Spacehab; Lucid exercises

<p>
<dt>03:14 a.m.
<dd>Readdy, Wilcutt and Akers conduct the hot-fire test of Atlantis' reaction
control system jets to verify their health of tomorrow's entry and landing

<p>
<dt>03:29 a.m.
<dd>Akers exercises

<p>
<dt>04:24 a.m.
<dd>U.S. PAO Opportunity with Readdy, Wilcutt, Akers and Lucid

<p>
<dt>05:44 a.m.
<dd>Readdy uses the SAREX gear for a personal contact

<p>
<dt>05:54 a.m.
<dd>Apt and Walz begin to stow the Spacehab module; Akers begins to stow
Atlantis' cabin

<p>
<dt>06:04 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt stows Atlantis' KU-band communications antenna

<p>
<dt>06:14 a.m.
<dd>Wilcutt uses the SAREX gear for a personal contact

<p>
<dt>06:24 a.m.
<dd>U.S. AUDIO ONLY PAO Opportunity with Wilcutt and Lucid

<p>
<dt>06:54 a.m.
<dd>Readdy, Wilcutt and Apt join Akers in cabin stow; Walz helps Lucid setup
a recumbent seat in the middeck for her for tomorrow's entry and landing

<p>
<dt>07:54 a.m.
<dd>Walz deactivates the Commercial Protein Crystal Growth experiment;
Lucid exercises

<p>
<dt>08:14 a.m.
<dd>Readdy conducts routine landing minus 1 day communications checks
through the Goldstone Tracking Station near the Dryden Flight Research
Center and the Merritt Island Tracking Station near the Kennedy Space
Center; Walz deactivates the radiation device

<p>
<dt>08:49 a.m.
<dd>Apt stows the VHF radio gear; Akers and Lucid stow Atlantis' bicycle
ergometer

<p>
<dt>10:24 a.m.
<dd>Private medical conference

<p>
<dt>11:24 a.m.
<dd>A backup opportunity for pre-landing communications checks through
Dryden and KSC

<p>
<dt>12:54 p.m.
<dd>Atlantis' crew sleep begins ( 9 hours )
</dl>



