<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>What's New</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/glogoppr.jpg">
<CENTER>South Florida Regional Planning Council</CENTER><br>

<CENTER><b>What's New in South Florida</b></CENTER>

<center><font size=+1>Eastward Ho! Local Government Resource Center
</font>
</center>
<HR>

Council staff will promote Eastward Ho! over the next two years through 
a
 number of additional activities which are designed to support local 
governments in the region.  A key undertaking in this area will be to
 establish a resource center for information about the Eastward Ho!
 initiative to promote coordinated strategies among outreach, education
 and training efforts, and to help identify opportunities for 
partnerships with existing initiatives that are consistent and 
supportive 
of Eastward Ho! development goals.<br><br>

In addition, staff will work to create a package of recommended actions 
for the 1997 and 1998 Sessions of the Florida Legislature, local 
governments, and others.<br><br>
 Topics to assess include:<br>
<ul>

<li> Incentives to assist local governments with infrastructure 
provision 
and environmental cleanup.

<li>Incentives or other strategies to make financing for infill 
development and redevelopment more available.

<li> Incentives/techniques to encourage job creation, especially in 
non-manufacturing sectors.

<li>Techniques to streamline approval and permitting processes for 
infill
 development and redevelopment.

<li> Incentives for local governments to update land development 
regulations.

Create an Eastward Ho! Corridor Infill Development and Redevelopment 
Ombudsman to be a contact point for developers and investors and to
assist projects that are consistent with Eastward Ho! goals through the 
local approval and permitting process.<br><br>

For additional information on <a href="../current/menu531.htm">
Eastward Ho!</a>, please contact <a href ="mailto:juliat@sfrpc.com"> Julia Trevarthen</a>.
<hr><br>



