<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>What's New</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/glogoppr.jpg">
<CENTER>South Florida Regional Planning Council</CENTER><br>

<CENTER><b>What's New in South Florida</b></CENTER>

<center><font size=+1>
Broward County's Human Service Delivery System Model Workshop
</font><br>December 9, 1996
</center>
<HR>

On December 9, 1996, from 1:00 pm to 5:00 pm, SFRPC staff will 
facilitate
 a workshop for the members of the Coordinating Council of Broward (CCB) 

to discuss a model for the human service delivery system in Broward 
County.  This workshop will be held at ArtServe, located adjacent to the 

Broward Regional Library at 1350 E. Sunrise Boulevard, Suite 100, in 
Fort Lauderdale.
<br><br>
The CCB's Mission Statement is "to develop a forum for ongoing health, 
education, and human services planning for Broward County in order to
 more efficiently and effectively meet community needs."  The CCB has
 determined that "the assessment process has demonstrated a lack of
 collaborative coordinated planning, delivery, and assessment resulting 
in fragmented, duplicated, and unmet community services and unfulfilled
 human needs."
<br><br>
In preparation for the workshop, SFRPC staff has conducted interviews
 with members of the CCB to identify expectations and concerns related
 to developing a model for the human service delivery system in Broward 
County.  In addition, staff is conducting a literature review of 
existing
 human service delivery systems in other large metropolitan regions and
 preparing an analysis of the strengths and weaknesses of these systems. 
 
Based on this analysis, the SFRPC will prepare an Issues and Options 
Report for discussion by members of the CCB at the workshop.  Finally, 
staff will prepare and distribute a final report summarizing the results 

of the workshop.  For additional information, please contact <a href ="mailto:rogburn@sfrpc.com"> Dick Ogburn</a> or <a href ="mailto:pchang@sfrpc.com"> Ping Chang</a>.
<br><br>
<b>Coordinating Council of Broward Member List</b><br>
Johnny Brown, Manager, Juvenile Justice Board, District X<br>
Ron Cochran, Sheriff, Broward Sheriff's Office<br>
James Garver, President/CEO, Broward Economic Development Council<br>
Andrea Guy, District Administrator, Children and Families, District X
<br>
Will Holcombe, President, Broward Community College<br>
Mason Jackson, Executive Director, Broward Employment & Training 
Administration
<br>
Kathy Koch, President, Ambit Marketing Communications<br>
Edith Lederberg, Executive Director, Area Agency on Aging<br>
Robert MacConnell, President, United Way<br>
Jasmin Shirley Moore, Director, HRS / Aids Patients Care / NW Health 
Center
<br>
Jack Moss (Chairman), Board Member, United Way<br>
Bill Norkunas, Director, Disabled Assisting the Disabled<br>
Jack Osterholt, County Administrator, Broward County<br>
Frank Petruzielo, Superintendent, Broward County School Board<br>
Gary Rubin, Executive Director, Jewish Federation of Broward County<br>
Frank Sacco, CEO, Memorial Healthcare System<br>
Wil Trower, President/CEO, North Broward Hospital District<br>
Rev. Thomas G. Wenski, Pierre Toussaint Haitian Catholic Center<br>
Bob Burton, Interim Executive Director, Coordinating Council of Broward
<br>
Skip Johnston, Chairman, CCB Steering Committee<br>

