<body background="../images/glogoppr.jpg">
<p align=center>South Florida Regional Planning Council</p>
<p align=center><b>What's New in South Florida</b> </p>
<p align=center><font size=4>Visioning in Lower Matecumbe Key </font></p>
<hr>
<p>The winter months of 1997 will mark an important turning point for the residents and business owners of Lower Matecumbe Key. At this time, residents, 
business owners and elected officials will have an opportunity to assembly for the purpose of discussing quality of life issues such as education, safety, health, 
economic development and water quality. This workshop will provide a body of knowledge, a setting and a technique for bringing people together to discuss 
issues of importance. In addition, a methodology will be developed to coordinate public policy issues. Council staff will organize and facilitate the <a href="../current/vision.htm">visioning</a> 
process. For more information, please contact <a href="mailto:esuarez@sfrpc.com">Evangeline Suarez. </a><br>
. </p>
<hr>
