<body background="../images/clogoppr.jpg">
<p align=center>South Florida Regional Planning Council</p>
<h3 align=center>Related Web Sites</h3>
<h3 align=center>Florida's Regional Planning Councils </h3>
<hr>
<p>The State of Florida's 67 counties are divided into eleven planning regions, each of which is represented by a Regional Planning Council (RPC). The other ten 
RPCs are identified below, together with the counties they represent. Active names will take you to the RPC web site. If you would like a summary directory of 
names, addresses and telephone numbers, go to the <a href="../council/menu15.htm">Regional Directory.</a> </p>
<p><a href="http://www.wfrpc.dst.fl.us/wfrpc/"><b>West Florida RPC</b></a><b> </b>- Bay, Escambia, Holmes, Okaloosa, Santa Rosa, Walton, Washington </p>
<p><a href="http://199.44.114.223/arpc/"><b>Apalachee RPC</b></a><b> </b>- Calhoun, Franklin, Gadsden, Gulf, Jackson, Jefferson, Leon, Liberty, Wakulla </p>
<p><a href="http://www.afn.org/~ncfrpc/"><b>North Central Florida RPC</b></a><b> </b>- Alachua, Bradford, Columbia, Dixie, Gilchrist, Hamilton, Lafayette, Madison, Suwannee, Taylor, Union</p>
<p><b>Northeast Florida RPC </b>- Baker, Clay, Duval, Flagler, Nassau, Putnam, St. Johns </p>
<p><b>Withlacoochee RPC </b>- Citrus, Hernando, Levy, Marion, Sumter </p>
<p><b>East Central Florida RPC </b>- Brevard, Lake, Orange, Osceola, Seminole, Volusia </p>
<p><a href="http://lakeland.tsolv.com/~cfrpc/"><b>Central Florida RPC</b></a><b> </b>- DeSoto, Hardee, Highlands, Okeechobee, Polk </p>
<p><a href="http://access.tampabayrpc.org/"><b>Tampa Bay RPC</b></a> - Hillsborough, Manatee, Pasco, Pinellas</p>
<p><a href="http://www.swfrpc.org"><b>Southwest Florida RPC</b></a><b> </b>- Charlotte, Collier, Glades, Hendry, Lee, Sarasota </p>
<p><a href="http://www.tcrpc.org/"><b>Treasure Coast RPC </b></a>- Indian River, Martin, Palm Beach, St. Lucie </p>
