<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Regional Profile and Identity</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/ylogoppr.jpg">
<CENTER>South Florida Regional Planning Council</CENTER><br>

<font size=+1><CENTER><b>Strategic Regional Policy Plan
for South Florida (SRPP)</b></CENTER>
<b><center>Regional Profile and Identity</center></b>
</font>
<center><img src="../images/rppsmall.gif" 
alt="rppknot.gif"></center>
<br>
<HR> 


The regional profile and identity will acquaint the reader with 
significant trends that have shaped South Florida and relates those 
trends to current and future issues affecting the Region.  It describes 
some of the expectations held for the Region in the areas of demography,
 economy, lifestyle and culture.  The description has been divided in 
four broad areas: Our People, Our Economy, Our Environment and Our
 Community.  South Florida is a complex and vibrant Region, full of 
opportunities for its residents and responsibilities for its leaders.<p>

South Florida, which has long been recognized as a tropical paradise,
 well-known for its beaches, tourist attractions and retirement 
population, has grown into a vibrant multi-cultural community, with an
 emerging role in the international economy.  The three-county region
 extends north from the Florida Keys to the dense urban settlements of
 Dade and Broward counties, and in many respects into the Palm Beaches. 
 The region must meet the challenge of actively developing an identity 
which will enable it to promote this transition.<p>

Some regional trends which can be discerned are
<ul>
<li> the continued population growth, led by international migration;
<li> the increasing globalization of the economy, based on trade and 
tourism;
<li> the increasing pressure on the strained natural environment; and
<li>the existence of a significant backlog in the region's 
infrastructure.
</ul>

<H4> <A HREF="profpeop.htm">Our 
People</A></H4>
<H4> <A HREF="profecon.htm">Our 
Economy</A></H4>
<H4> <A HREF="profenvi.htm">Our 
Environment</A></H4>

<H4> <A HREF="profcomm.htm">Our 
Community</A> </H4>


