<html>

<head>
<title>EAR ALMANAC</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="../images/plogoppr.jpg">
<p align=center>South Florida Regional Planning Council </p>
<p align=center><font size=4><b>Council Programs</b></font></p>
<p align=center><font size=4><b>Evaluation and Appraisal Report Almanac</b></font></p>
<hr>
<p><font size=3>Recognizing that the Evaluation and Appraisal Report (EAR) process is not going to go away, the South Florida Regional Planning Council is preparing a 
compendium of information related to EAR requirements. The purpose of the EAR Almanac will be to keep </font><a href="../websites/wwwsfmun.htm"><font size=3>local governments</font></a><font size=3> current on issues that will affect 
them in the upcoming EAR cycle. The Almanac will be updated regularly and will contain the following:</font></p>
<ul>
<li><font size=3>Suggestions on how to keep plans updated on an annual basis </font></li>
<li><font size=3>A section outlining necessary steps and requirements for preparing an EAR </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Updates on changes in the statutes, rules and regional policy plans </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Analysis of issues which can affect local plans so as to provide problems and/or opportunities </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Information provided by DCA and the Shimberg Center on the Affordable Housing Needs Assessment Methodology </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Coastal Land Inventory and Monitoring System - information to be provided by SFRPC.</font> </li>
</ul>
<p><font size=4><b><i>WE WELCOME YOUR IDEAS ON THIS IMPORTANT PROJECT!!</i></b></font> </p>
<hr>
<p align=center><b>[ </b><a href="../council/menu1.htm"><b>The Council</b></a> | <a href="../whatsnew/menu2.htm"><b>What's New</b></a> | <a href="../websites/menu3.htm"><b>Related Web Sites</b></a> | <a href="../region/menu4.htm"><b>Our Region</b></a> | <a href="../current/menu5.htm"><b>Current Issues</b></a> ] </p>
