sustainable, and competitive South Florida.</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>96-1104</td><td valign=top>11/12/96</td><td valign=top>Funding application for the Cleveland Road 
Bridge and Daytonia Road Bridge. Florida 
Department of Transportation. Miami Beach, 
Dade County. </td><td valign=top>Council staff finds the project to be generally consistent with <i>Strategic Regional Policy Plan 
for South Florida</i>. However, Council staff recommends that pre-cautionary measures be 
incorporated into the project to limit adverse impacts on water quality, the West Indian 
Manatee and other wildlife habitats. The goals and policies of the <i>Strategic Regional Policy 
Plan for South Florida </i>pertaining to natural resources of regional significance should be 
considered.</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>96-1105</td><td valign=top>11/18/96</td><td valign=top>The applicant proposes to expand an existing 
marina. Len-Hal Realty, Inc. Hollywood, 
Broward County. Corps# 198821141 
(IP-CB). DEP# 062894416</td><td valign=top>Council staff expressed concern about the impacts this project could have on the water quality, 
