corresponding land development regulations. Staff recommends that if this permit is granted the 
impacts to the natural systems be minimized to the greatest extent feasible, the permit grantor 
determine the extent of sensitive marine life and vegetative communities in the vicinity and 
require protection and/or mitigation of disturbed habitat. The goals and policies of the 
<i>Strategic Regional Policy Plan for South Florida</i> pertaining to natural resources of regional 
significance should be considered.</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>96-1106</td><td valign=top>11/18/96</td><td valign=top>The applicant proposes to fill wetlands to 
construct a single family residence. Orestes 
Gutierrez. Cudjoe Key, Monroe County. 
Corps# 199604093 (IP-EJ). DEP# 
442936585</td><td valign=top>Council staff expressed concern about the impacts this project could have on the water quality, 
wildlife habitat and the overall ecological integrity of the region. The project should be 
consistent with the goals and policies of the Monroe County comprehensive plan and its 
