<HEAD>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="Content-Type" CONTENT="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<TITLE> EV READY BROWARD Core</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.03z">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/plogoppr.jpg">
<P>
<CENTER>South Florida Regional Planning Council<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4>Special Projects and Studies<BR>
<BR>
</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=4>EV READY BROWARD <BR>
Paving the Way for Electric Vehicles</FONT></B> <BR>
<BR>
Broward County has been selected as one of the ten (10) communities
in the United States to become ready for electric vehicles in
the near future. The South Florida Regional Planning Council,
in partnership with the Department of Energy and Transportation,
the Electric Vehicle Association of the Americas, the Electric
Transportation Coalition and Florida Alliance for Clean Technologies,
is helping to make this happen. <BR>
<BR>
With Board of Directors and five (5) operating committees, consisting
of public and private sectors, an effort to prepare infrastructure
systems and the policy framework necessary to support electric
vehicles is well under way. The programs goals are for Broward
County to be ready for large scale introductions of electric vehicles
in two years, to leave in place 750 operating electric vehicles
and 25 buses and to offer to other Florida communities a model
for preparing the way for EVs. <BR>
<BR>
For additional information on EV Ready Broward, please contact
<A href="mailto:gadson@sfrpc.com">George E. Gadson</A>. <BR>
<BR>
