<html>

<head>
<title>REGIONAL CAPITAL FACILITIES INVENTORY</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="../images/plogoppr.jpg">
<p align=center>South Florida Regional Planning Council</p>
<p align=center><font size=4>Council Programs</font></p>
<p align=center><font size=4>Regional Capital Facilities Inventory</font></p>
<hr>
<p><font size=3>Recognizing that the Region's ability to move forward depends on the quality of its capital facilities, the South Florida Regional Planning Council has undertaken 
a project to inventory its most significant capital facilities. The focus of this project is on facilities which have the potential to impact all or a large portion of the 
region. The Regional Capital Facilities Inventory will identify facilities in several areas:</font></p>
<ul>
<li><font size=3>Transportation </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Public Safety </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Potable Water </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Solid Waste </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Recreation and Open Space </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Education </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Energy </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Telecommunications </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Economic and Business Resources </font></li>
<li><font size=3>Miscellaneous </font></li>
</ul>
<p><font size=3>The end product will be an Atlas of Regional Capital Facilities. Periodic updates are expected to occur on a regular bases. The Atlas will be available in digital 
and hard copy format.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>While it is expected that the Atlas will be a handy planning tool, its real value will lie in its utility as a reference document and as a tool for economic 
development planning. Those agencies seeking to market the South Florida Region will find the information they need contained in a single, attractive, easy to 
use document.</font></p>
<p><font size=3>For additional information on regional capital facilities, please contact </font><a href="mailto:bobd@sfrpc.com"><font size=3>Bob Daniels</font></a><font size=3>.</font></p>
<hr>
