<TITLE>Southeast Florida 2025</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.03z">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/wlogoppr.jpg">
<P>
<CENTER>South Florida Regional Planning Council<BR>
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4>Overview</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4>Southeast Florida 2025: An Investment
Strategy for the Future</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="../images/2025sm.gif" border=0></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
When Senate Bill No. 3062 was first enacted on May 23, 1994, Southeast
Florida 2025 was formed. Initiated by Senator Kenneth Jenne, Chairman
of the Steering Committee of 35, Southeast Florida 2025 serves
as a catalyst for comprehensive planning of Southeast Florida's
future. The process provides an environment where elected leadership
of the region and individuals from the business community can
focus on such areas as education, regional governance, law enforcement,
health, social issues, transportation, economic development, infrastructure
and natural systems. The process continues to foster consensus-based
strategies for investing in Southeast Florida's future through
partnership building and regional collaboration and cooperation.
In an effort to realize the vision for Southeast Florida, the
Action Teams listed below were formed by the Steering Committee.
Community Leaders were recruited to serve as Team Facilitators
and Team members in order to move the Southeast Florida 2025 project
from vision to action.<BR>
<HR>
<P>
