<TITLE>Noticeof Hazardous Materials</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.03z">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<CENTER> <BODY BACKGROUND="../images/plogoppr.jpg">South Florida
Regional Planning Council<BR>
<BR>

</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4>Council Programs</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4>Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC)</FONT></B>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
<B>NOTICE OF PUBLIC AVAILABILITY<BR>
OF HAZARDOUS MATERIALS INFORMATION<BR>
<BR>
<B>THE DISTRICT XI LOCAL EMERGENCY PLANNING COMMITTEE ANNOUNCES
<BR>
THE PUBLIC AVAILABILITY OF THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION.</B></B>
<BR>
<BR>
Pursuant to Section 324 of the Emergency Planning and Community
Right-to-know Act, known as the Title III of the Superfund Amendments
and Reauthorization Act (SARA) the following information is available
to the public upon request during business hours 8:30 to 5:30
Monday through Friday from the Local Emergency Planning Committee
(LEPC) in District XI.<BR>
<BR>
<DL>
<DT>
<DD>Materials Safety Data Sheets (MSDS)<BR>
Hazardous Chemical Inventory Forms<BR>
Emergency Follow Up Notices<BR>
District XI Hazardous Materials Emergency Plan<BR>
<BR>
</DL>
<P>
District XI consists of Broward, Dade and Monroe Counties. SARA
Title III requires that any business using certain hazardous chemicals
register with state and local agencies. If you have never registered,
contact the agency listed below immediately for more information.
If you have previously complied, be sure you are up to date. Penalties
for failure to comply are severe. SARA Title III How-to-Comply
Handbooks are available at the LEPC.  For additional information,
please contact <A href ="mailto:dam@sfrpc.com">Doris Mitchell</A>.
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
