<HEAD>
<TITLE>Natural Environment Research Council</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerclarg.gif" ALT="NERC"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>The Environmental Issues</H2>
<HR>
<P></p>
<p>
NERC's challenge is to generate knowledge and understanding of the natural 
environment and to develop technologies and skills to apply that knowledge.  
The issues concerning the environment and man's impact on natural processes 
are high in the priorities of government, industry, commerce and academia.  
the NERC environmental agenda over the next decade will include:
</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Biodiversity</b> - understanding and protection of biodiversity</li>

<li><b>Environmental risks and hazards</b> including release of genetically modified 
organisms, prediction of extreme events and rapid environmental assessments 
for operational needs</li>

<li><b>Global change</b> including predictions on a range of time and space 
scales</li>

<li><b>Natural resources</b> - management of land, water and the coastal zone, the 
identification and exploitation of land-, freshwater- and marine-based 
resources and their sustainability</li>

<li><b>Pollution</b>  of air, land, sea and freshwater in relation to 
environmental and human health</li>

<li><b>Waste</b> management, bioremediation and land restoration</li>
</ul>
<p>
Various publications (including the NERC Corporate Plan and Environmental Direction)
are available from <A HREF="mailto:fmb@wpo.nerc.ac.uk">Frances Banks</A>,
NERC Communications Section.
<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/index.html"><IMG SRC="/images/logoicon.gif" ALIGN="middle"
>To the NERC home page</A>
<HR>
Comments may be sent to:
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk</A></ADDRESS>
