<HEAD>
<TITLE>General Financial Information</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>General Financial Information</H2>
<p>
About half of our Science Budget goes to UK universities via research 
grants, fellowships and studentships to individuals, or via contracts with 
specialist groups located within universities such as the Centre for 
Population Biology at Imperial College, London. 
</p><p>
We also have our own centres of excellence for studies of earth, water, 
land and air.  Their work is impartial and is frequently long-term to study 
natural cycles and slow, cumulative processes.  
</p><p>
Substantial support is provided to NERC-funded scientists and to the 
science community through our Scientific Services, such as the use of 
<a href="http://www.soc.soton.ac.uk/RVS/rvsindex.html">Royal 
Research Ships</a>, airborne remote sensing aircraft, analytical laboratories 
and specialist equipment pools.
</p>
<p>
</p>
<hr>
<p></p>
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC="/images/logoicon.gif" ALIGN="middle"
>To the NERC home page</A>
<HR>
Comments may be sent to:
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk
</A></ADDRESS> 
