<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Funding Routes, Training, Careers</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>Funding Routes, Training, Careers</H2>
<p>
Four main routes are used to fund the best science in universities and in 
NERC's own research establishments. Under Thematic Research NERC selects 
themes within its mission which are particularly important, topical or 
under-investigated, and invites relevant applications.  For Non-Thematic 
Research NERC will consider proposals in any area covered by the NERC 
mission.  Core Strategic Funding supports longer term research, survey or 
monitoring carried out mainly at NERC's own establishments. Infrastructure 
Funding provides essential support, equipment, services and facilities for 
the NERC Community.
</p>
<p>
Details of NERC's funding can be found in the leaflet <i>"NERC at work" 
</i>(available from <A HREF="mailto:fmb@wpo.nerc.ac.uk">
Frances Banks</A>, NERC Communications Section).

</P>
<P>
See also:<BR>
</P>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="/awards/">Awards and Training</A> Home Page
 including <a href="/awards/fundop">Funding Opportunities within NERC
</a>
</LI>
<LI>
<A HREF="/eos/ao/wwwaq.htm">Earth Observation Announcements of Opportunity
</LI>
</UL>
<hr>

<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC="/images/logoicon.gif" ALIGN="middle"
>To the NERC home page</A>
