<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Delivering the Mission</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>Delivering the Mission</H2>
<p>

The results of NERC-funded basic research are normally published as 
scientific papers.  Contract work is reported confidientially to customers, 
but this may also be published later in the open literature.  Other 
important outputs include the development of technologies such as 
specialised instruments and software/modelling packages, some of which have 
led to patents and commercially exploitable products.  Advice on policy to 
Government and evidence to Parliamentary Committees are other facets of our 
output.
</p>
<p>
<h3>The Data Resource</h3>
<p>
One of our strategic aims is to collect, curate, interpret and supply 
<a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/databrochure.html">
environmental data</a>.  To achieve this aim, NERC has established seven 
<a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/corp_data_centres.html">Data 
Centres</a> to manage material from its own programmes together with data 
deposited by others.  A data directory is available and we make data readily 
accessible to users, together with information and advice.
</p>

<p></p>
<hr>

<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/index.html"><IMG SRC="/images/logoicon.gif" ALIGN="middle"
>To the NERC home page</A>
<HR>
Comments may be sent to:
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk
