<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Public Understanding of Science</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>Public Understanding of Science</H2>
<p></p>
<h3>Spreading the Message</h3>  
<p>

Awareness of human impact on the environment has grown over the last two 
decades.  Some words and concepts are now firmly embedded in our language 
and culture.  But public perceptions of  science and technology may still 
be negative: failure to arrest adverse trends, such as a thinning ozone 
layer or the destruction of hedgerows, may be seen as a failure of science. 
As well as producing our normal reports materials and events we are now 
telling a wider audience  how our science matters to everyday life. We are 
expanding our Schools Programme and we take part in science exhibitions and 
initiatives, such as the Edinburgh Science Festival, and the Science, 
Engineering and Technology Week (SET7).  Taking the environmental message 
to the public at large, inspiring the next generation with the excitement 
of science, are major challenges we aim to meet.

</p>
<hr>
<p></p>
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC="/images/logoicon.gif" ALIGN="middle"
>To the NERC home page</A>
<HR>
Comments may be sent to:
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk
</A></ADDRESS> 
