<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Internet Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY><H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif"></H1>
<HR>
<H2>Internet Services</H2>
<P>The array of information services on the Internet is vast, inconstant, and poorly indexed.
You will undoubtedly build up your own <I>hot list</I> of services which you find useful
but here are three lists of useful starting points for exploration of the Internet. The first points to services in the UK; the <A HREF="#internet"
>second</A> to services on the Internet at large, and the <A HREF="#others"
>third</A> to other information sources of interest.
</P><HR>
<H3>UK Services</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Information sources within or about <A HREF="/corp_innerc.html">NERC</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.doc.mmu.ac.uk/aric/arichome.html">The Atmospheric
Research and Information Centre</A>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.doc.mmu.ac.uk/aric/gcciphm.html">The Global 
Climate Change Information Programme</A>
</LI>
</UL>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.muscat.co.uk/ccdp/spri/wdccg.html">Ice and Snow database
</A>(part of the World Data Centre C (Galciology) section.
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.netskills.ac.uk/">Internet for Everyone</A>, a WWW-based
learning course on using the Internet (part of the Netskills ITTI initiative).</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.icbl.hw.ac.uk/itti/">ITTI</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://mailbase.ac.uk/">Mailbase</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://midas.ac.uk/">MIDAS</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nhm.ac.uk/">Natural History Museum</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.niss.ac.uk/">NISS Information Gateway</A>
</LI> 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hensa.ac.uk/">UK Higher Education Software Archive</A> (HENSA)
</LI>
<LI>CHEST
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.niss.ac.uk/chest/messenger.html">CHEST Messenger</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.niss.ac.uk/chest/recent-news.html">CHEST Recent News</A>
</LI>
</UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.epsrc.ac.uk/hpc/introduction.html">UK High Performance Computing facilities</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://src.doc.ic.ac.uk/all-uk.html">UK World Wide Web servers</A>
</LI>
<LI>An alternative entr&eacute;e to the set of UK WWW servers - <A HREF="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/misc/uk/intro.html"
>an active map of the UK</A>
</LI>
<LI><A NAME="sigweb">A</A> Special Interest Group for the UK and Ireland
on the World Wide Web -
<A HREF="http://www.qub.ac.uk/sigweb/">SIGWEB</A>.
</LI>
<LI>An experimental <A HREF="http://http1.brunel.ac.uk:8080/wlu.html">WWW to X.500 gateway</A>.
</LI>
<LI>A Gopher to X.500 gateway covering <A HREF="gopher://dir.ic.ac.uk:7777/1"
>all countries</A> or just <A HREF="gopher://dir.ic.ac.uk:7777/1Mc%3dGB">
Great Britain</A>.
<P>The X.500 directory service contains contact information such as e-mail addresses
for many institutions in the UK, Europe and North America.
</P><P></P></LI>
</UL><HR>
<A NAME="internet"><H3>Internet Services</H3></A>
<P>The services below are, in general, outside the UK and therefore people in the UK will find retrieval of information from them slower than from the UK.</P><P
>You might want to consider using the <A HREF="proxy.html">HENSA public proxy service</A> to speed up access to these documents.</P><P></P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="publish.html">Providing information via the World Wide Web</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/StartingPoints/NetworkStartingPoints.html"
>Starting points for Internet exploration</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://webcrawler.com/">
Web Crawler</A> - a searchable catalogue built by a <I>robot</I> which
searches and indexes the contents of documents on the Web
</LI>
<LI>
<A HREF="http://lycos.cs.cmu.edu/lycos-form.html">Lycos</A>
is another useful Web searching tool; it is also a searchable catalogue
built by a robot which searches and indexes the contents of documents on the Web
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://nearnet.gnn.com/gnn/wic/newrescat.toc.html">The Whole Internet Catalogue</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://cuiwww.unige.ch/w3catalog">A searchable WWW catalogue</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cs.colorado.edu/home/mcbryan/WWWW.html">WWW Worm</A>
- another searchable catalogue
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://kaos.erin.gov.au/other_servers/category/server_category.html"
>Environmental servers</A>
</LI>
<LI>WWW servers by <A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/bySubject/Overview.html"
>subject</A>
</LI>
<LI>WWW servers by <A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/WWW/Geographical.html"
>geographical location</A>
</LI>
<LI>Data sources by <A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/ByAccess.html"
>type</A> of access method
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.internic.net/">The Internet Network Information Center</A> (NIC)
</LI>
<LI>List of <A HREF="http://www.fcm.missouri.edu/book/gdindex.htm">Internet Navigation Guides</A>
</LI>
</UL><HR>
<A NAME="others"><H3>Other Useful Information Sources</H3></A>
<P> </P><P></P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="res_councils.html">Other Research Councils and their Institutes</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.open.gov.uk/">The CCTA Government Information Service</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="suppliers.html">Suppliers' Home Pages</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="/events/">Events</A> 
</LI>
</P><P></P>
</UL><HR>
<P></P><P>
<H3><I>Caveat</I></H3>
<P>Most of the above services (and those found through them) are not provided by
<A HREF="/ncs/">NERC Computer Services</A> who, therefore, accept no
responsibility for the reliability of the services or the accuracy of the information obtained
through them.
</P><P></P>
Comments may be sent to:
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">
www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk</A></ADDRESS>
