<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>What's New on the NERC WWW</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerclarg.gif" ALT="NERC"></H1>
<hr>
<p></P>
<H2>What's New</H2>
<hr>
<P>Comments and suggestions may be sent to
<A HREF="mailto:www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">www-support@ncs.nerc.ac.uk</A>
</P>
<P></P>
<UL>
<LI>November 28th 1996<P></P>
The Geophysical Equipment Pool have trial Web pages at <A HREF="http://www.glg.ed.ac.uk/home/gep/gep">http://www.glg.ed.ac.uk/home/gep/gep.</A>
<P></P>
<LI>November 22nd 1996<P></P>
The UK NERC Community Research Project, Atmospheric Chemistry Studies in the Ocean Environment (ACSOE), now has a web site at <A HREF="http://www.uea.ac.uk/~e011/acsoe/acsoe.html">http://www.uea.ac.uk/~e011/acsoe/acsoe.html.</A>
<P></P>
<LI>November 19th 1996<P></P>
The Remote Sensing Applications Development Unit (RSADU), Southampton, now has a web site at <A HREF="http://www.soc.soton.ac.uk/RSADU">http://www.soc.soton.ac.uk/RSADU.</A>
<P></P>
<LI>October 29th 1996<P></P>
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/awards/rpgt.htm">Review of Postgraduate Education and Training, Advanced MSc courses.</A>
<P></P>
<LI>October 16th 1996<P></P>
NOW ON THE WEB: <A HREF="http://www.globalchange.org/">GLOBAL CLIMATE CHANGE DIGEST</A><BR>
Global Climate Change Digest is a  unique comprehensive guide to published material on global climate change and ozone depletion now available on the World Wide Web.
<P></P>
<LI>October 15th 1996<P></P>
NERC has made available funds for a thematic programme <A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/awards/benbo.htm">The Deep Ocean BENthic BOundary Layer (BENBO)</A>
<P></P>
<li>September 24th 1996<p></p>
The <a href="http://thesis.newsint.co.uk/">Times Higher Education Supplement
Internet Service</a> is now available.
 This site also hosts the <a href="http://thesis.newsint.co.uk/NCIHE/Dearing.html">
Dearing Comittee</a> pages.
</li><p></p>
<li>September 23rd 1996<p></p>
A new NERC programme, <A href="http://www.nerc-oxford.ac.uk/edge/">
NERC Ecological Dynamics and Genes Programme (EDGE)</a>
has been set up. The Web page gives further details for outline bids and
makes the appropriate forms available.
</li><p></p>
<li>New <a href="http://www.nkw.ac.uk/kwls">Keyworth Local Support</a>
web pages are now available. They are also reachable via <a href="corp_nercorg.html">
NERC Organisation</a>, <a href="/ncs/">NERC Computer Services</a>, on the
NERC web pages.
</li><p></p>
<li>September 16th 1996<p></p>
<a href="http://www.swwater.co.uk/">South West Water</a> Devon, has now
launched its site on the Internet. Amongst other things, it includes a Links
page to other Web sites of environmental interest.
</li>
<p></p>
<li>September 10th 1996<p></p>
The report from the <a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/ukgeroff/strategy.htm">
UK National Strategy for Global Environmental Research (GER)</a>
has been released on the WWW, under the <a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/ukgeroff/welcome.htm">
GER Home Page</a>.
This report explores the importance of GER in terms of relevance to society
and the economy and committments to international policy agreements and
science programmes.
</li>
<p></p>
<li>September 9th 1996<p></p>
<b>Welcome to the new Corporate NERC WWW pages</b>. As you can see, some 
changes
have been made to the way in which the information is laid out, allowing
 for further new, lower level, pages to be added more easily in the future.
</li>
<p></p>
<li>August 30th 1996<p></p>
A link has been added to the <a href="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/joint_res_councils.html">
Joint Research Councils home page</a> for a 
<a href="http://www.bubl.bath.ac.uk/BUBL/RCL.html">Listing of Research Council
Libraries in the UK</a>, part of the <a href="http://www.bubl.bath.ac.uk/BUBL/">
BUBL (Bulletin Board for Librarians)</a>.</li>
<p></p>
<li>August 13th 1996<p></p>
<a href="http://www.soc.soton.ac.uk/RVS/rvsindex.html">Research Vessel
Services</a> are linked into the <a href="corp_nercorg.html">NERC Organisation
</a> page.
<p></p>
 <a href="http://www.niss.ac.uk/reference/mapobi/obi.html">OPACS in
Britain and Ireland (OBI)</a> pages are available. They contain a directory
of library catalogues and services, maintained by
<a href="http://www.niss.ac.uk/">NISS</a>.
<p></p>
The <a href="http://www.niss.ac.uk/education/jisc/pub/strategy.html">
JISC Five Year Strategy 1996-2001</a>
 is available on the Web. JISC is the Joint Information Systems Committee.
<p></p>
A new section has been added to the NISS Noticeboard called <a href="http://www.niss.ac.uk/noticeboard/#announce">Announcements and Press Releases</a>
.
<p></p>
The <a href="http://europa.eu.int/">European Commission</a>
 has recently changed its address
on the WWW. The EUROPA server contains information on EU institutions
 and their activities.
<p></p>
The <a href="http://www.cis.rl.ac.uk/cclubs/crisp/">Community Club
Research Information Service Project (CRISP)</a>
has been announced by the <a href="http://www.cis.rl.ac.uk/cclubs.html">EPSRC 
Community Clubs</a> recently. The goal of CRISP is to provide
a single search index for researchers from UK academia and industry
covering both projects
and areas of research. <p></p>
<li>August 1st 1996<p></p>
NERC has made available funds for a thematic programme
<a href="/awards/dema.htm">Development of Marine Animals Special Topic (DEMA)</a>
. This is reachable via the <a href="/awards/index.html">A & T </a> home page.
<p></p>
The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) will be making future
Announcements of Opportunity for its Mission to Planet Earth (MTPE) available
electronically on the release date on the <a href="http://www.hq.nasa.gov/office/mtpe">
MTPE Home Page</a>, under MTPE Research Announcements. As these documents
will be available via the Internet, the Earth Observation Programme Office at NERC will
no longer be distributing copies by post. NERC contact: <a href="mailto:ajri@wpo.nerc.ac.uk">
Andrew Richardson</a>.
</li><p></p>
<li>July 31st 1996<p></p>
The NERC Bulletin Board for NISS & CHEST information has 
been removed. However, information can be found under the
<a href="http://www.niss.ac.uk/">NISS</a> and
<a href="http://www.chest.ac.uk/">CHEST</a> own pages.</li><p></p>
<li>July 24th 1996<p></p>
For those interested in legal issues and the Internet, a couple of URLs
that may be of interest are:
<a href="http://www.twobirds.com/">Bird and Bird (law firm)</a> and 
<a href="http://www.ftech.net/webspace/netlaw">Nick Lockett (Barrister)</a>.
<p></p>
NERC has been signed up for access to the <a href="http://www.netfirst.ac.uk/">
NetFirst database</a>. NetFirst contains bibliographic citations - complete with summary descriptions
and subject headings - describing Internet accessible resources, including
WWW pages, interest groups, library catalogues, FTP sites, Internet
services, Gopher servers, electronic journals and newsletters. This is
arranged via a <a href="http://www.chest.ac.uk/datasets/netfirst/contents.html">
CHEST agreement</a> with the service made available via the <a href="
http://www.niss.ac.uk/cgi-bin/siteadmlst.pl">NISS Information
Gateway ATHENA access system</a>. 
<p></p>
The administrator of the deal for the NERC is <a href="mailto:J.Beckett@nerc.ac.uk">John Beckett, ITE Library</a> 

<p></p>
</li>
<li>July 22nd 1996<p></p>
<a href="http://www.gnet.org/">The Global Network of Environment and
Technology (GNET)</a> provides environmental and technical professionals
with news summaries, regulatory information, technical profiles, market trends
etc.
<p></p></li>
<li>July 19th 1996<p></p>
There are now pages on the Web for the <a href="http://www.epsrc.ac.uk/hpc/hpc97/">
Project HPC (High Performance Computing) 97</a>
- Joint Research Councils' HPC Procurement, in which NERC has almost a quarter
stake.</li>
<p></p>
<li>July 5th 1996<p></p>
The <a href="http://www.stir.ac.uk/departments/NaturalSciences/nercunit/UAB-home.html">
NERC Unit of Aquatic Biochemistry</a> at Stirling are now on the WWW.
<p></p>
Hull University have an on-going project <a href="
http://www.hull.ac.uk/HumberNet/">
HumberNet</a> which takes 
measurements of the air, sea, tides and weather from East Yorkshire and surrounding
areas.
</li>
<p></p>
<LI>January to June 1996 "Whats New" items are under <A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/jan-june-96.html">What Was New - Jan-June 1996</A>
<P></P>
<LI>July to December 1995 "What's New" items are under <A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/july-dec-95.html">
What Was New - July-Dec 1995</A></LI>
<P></P>
<LI>January to June 1995 &quot;What's New&quot; items are under
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/jan-june-95.html">What Was New - Jan-June 1995</A>
<P></P></LI>
<LI>Pre-January 1995 &quot;What's New&quot; items are under
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/june-dec-94.html">What Was New - Pre-1995</A>
<P></P></LI>
</UL>
