<head>
<title>NERC Scientific Services Data Centre</title>
</head>
<body>
<H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerclarg.gif" ALT="NERC"></H1>
<H2><CENTRE>NERC SCIENTIFIC SERVICES DATA CENTRE
</CENTRE></H2>
<HR><p>

<H2>Introduction</H2><P>

The NERC Scientific Services Data Centre (NSSDC) was formed in April 1995 from the Data Services 
section of NERC Computer Services.   The Data Centre has responsibility for the stewardship of 
NERCs airborne remotely sensed data and of satellite data acquired by NERC from commercial 
sources.   The Data Centre also ensures that, where appropriate, adequate stewardship is 
accorded to other data acquired by NSS, so that such data are managed as a resource for the 
scientific community.<P>


<H3>The Service</H3><P>

NSSDC administers a central archive and catalogue of satellite and airborne data.   It will 
undertake satellite data availability searches from internal and external archives on behalf 
of the NERC-funded community.   The Data Centre holds a modest budget for new acquisitions in 
support of NERC programmes and will order data for the NERC community.   Such central purchasing 
aims at avoiding replication of purchase and ensures custodianship of valuable data.  The Data 
Centre will also provide advice on copyright regulations pertaining to the use of commercial 
satellite data.<P>

<H3>The Image Archive</H3><P>

Currently the central Image Archive contains some 5500 reels of remotely sensed data.  
Approximately 2000 tapes hold commercial satellite data, predominantly Landsat Thematic 
Mapper (TM) and Multispectral Scanner (MSS) scenes, supplemented by a small SPOT archive and 
minor holdings of a range of experimental sensors.   There is a large archive of NERC airborne 
campaign data (1982 to present), where the holdings are mainly Airborne Thematic Mapper (ATM) 
data, with some hyperspectral sensor data.<P>

Additionally, the NSSDC holds the master archive of film negatives from the NERC airborne 
campaign photography, together with all ancillary information allied to the campaigns (maps,
annual flight reports, calibration information etc.)<P>

<H3>Access and Charges</H3><P>

Under agreements with data suppliers, the NERC-funded community has access to the total archive.   
Other groups have access only to data acquired by NERC services; for example, the airborne 
campaign data.<P>

No charge is made for general information, searches or meta-data.   NERC-funded users receive 
digital data free of charge.  Higher Education Institutions receive data at the marginal cost 
of meeting their requests.   All other use of NERC data is charged at a commercial rate.<P>

<H3>NERC Corporate Data Holdings</H3><P>

NSSDC maintains the NERC Corporate Data Directory and acts as initial point of contact for 
information for general enquiries on <A HREF="/databrochure.html">NERC data holdings</A>.<P>

<H2>Contact:</H2><P>

<ADDRESS>Mrs Angela Morrison<BR>
NSS Data Centre<BR>
Holbrook House<BR>
Station Road<BR>
Swindon SN1 1DE<BR>
Tel: 01793 411955<BR>
Fax: 01793 411959<p>

<P>Author: <I><A HREF="mailto:a.j.morrison@nss.nerc.ac.uk">a.j.morrison@nss.nerc.ac.uk</A>.</I></P>
</address>
<P>Last updated and checked on June 19th 1996.</P>
