<H1><IMG SRC="/images/ncs.gif" ALIGN="middle"> Look up NERC mail addresses</H1>
<HR>
<P><A NAME="top">You</A> may use this form to query the NERC
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/ncs/curd/">Central User
Registration Database</A> for mail addresses &amp; telephone numbers of NERC
staff.
</P>
<P>(Those at NERC sites may use a
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/ncs/curd/nercform.html">more flexible form</A>.)</P>
<P>
The search is by a person's name (see <A HREF="#note1">below</A>), returning
<I>approximate</I> matches if no exact match can be found (see
<A HREF="#note2">below</A>).
</P>
<P>

</P>
<FORM ACTION="/cgi-bin/form-lookup" METHOD="GET">
<P>Name(s) for which to search
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="name" SIZE="40">
</P>
<P>
You may now
<INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="submit"> the query,
<A HREF="#criteria">modify the query criteria</A>, or 
<INPUT TYPE="reset" VALUE="reset"> the form.
</P>
<HR> 
<P><IMG SRC="http://www.npm.ac.uk/images.symbols/golf-b.gif">
<A NAME="criteria">The</A> following buttons increase the amount of data
returned:
</P>
<P>
<INPUT TYPE="hidden" NAME="type" VALUE="zs">
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="flag" VALUE="a"> Show the postal address.<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="flag" VALUE="m"> Show the person's actual mailbox,
if known, as well as the <I>institutional</I> or <I>canonical</I> mail address
(the latter is always shown if the person has registered their preferred
mailbox).<BR>
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="flag" VALUE="e"> Include in the search the records
of people who have left NERC employment.
</P>
<P>
<A HREF="#top">To the top of the form.</A>
</P>
<HR>
<H3>
<IMG SRC="http://www.npm.ac.uk/images.symbols/golf-b.gif"> Notes</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A NAME="note1">Names</A> may be entered as one of -
<UL>
<LI> Surname
</LI>
<LI> Initial.Surname
</LI>
<LI> Firstname.Surname
</LI>
</UL>If more than one name is given, they should be separated by spaces. It does
not matter whether names are given in upper- or lower-case.
</LI>
<LI><A NAME="note2">For</A> approximate matches, only the person's name,
institute and location are returned. This is to avoid returning large amounts of
irrelevant data. You may click on a person's name to see all the details you
requested.
<BR> Such queries take several seconds. Please be patient.
</LI>
</UL>
