<body bgcolor=#ffffff><p>

<h1>Fellowships Booklet</h1>
<p>

<p>

FELLOWSHIPS - 1996/97 Edition<p>

<p>

<p>

This booklet sets out the terms and conditions of the Fellowship Schemes which are administered<p>

by the Natural Environment Research Council (NERC).  NERC will be glad to advise on any<p>

queries or to provide further information by letter or telephone.<p>

<p>

Separate booklets are available dealing with the award of NERC Studentships and Research<p>

Grants.<p>

<p>

Fellowships are described as 'AWARDS' and to avoid confusion enquirers are asked not to refer<p>

to these as 'grants' since the latter term may be construed as referring to NERC Research Grants.<p>

<p>

All enquiries concerning NERC Fellowships should be addressed to:<p>

<p>

Natural Environment Research Council<p>


<ul>
  <li><b>Awards and Training Section</li>
  <li>Polaris House</li>
  <li>North Star Avenue</li>
  <li>SWINDON      SN2 1EU</li>
  <li>Telephone:     (01793) 411562</li>
  <li>Fax:           (01793) 411616</li>
  <li><a href="mailto:tawards@wpo.nerc.ac.uk">E_Mail
tawards@wpo.nerc.ac.uk</a></li>
</b></ul>
<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b><p>

DATES FOR APPLICATIONS<p>


<ul>
  <li></li>
  <li>For all Fellowship schemes:</li>
  <li></li>
  <li>Closing Date:       30 September 1996</li>
  <li></li>
  <li>Interviews:         Early March</li>
  <li></li>
  <li>Results by the end of:   April</li>
</b></ul>
<p>

<hr>
<p>

<h2>The Council reserves the right to change any of these
regulations from time to time as the Council may think fit,
without prior notification.</h2>
<hr>
<p>

<b><p>

Foreword</b><p>

The Natural Environment Research Council has introduced a new and extended Research<p>

Fellowship scheme to complete its range of personal career awards for outstanding environmental<p>

scientists. The scheme is intended to provide structured research career opportunities over a<p>

longer term with a greater possibility of continuity. This will enable  prime movers' greater<p>

opportunity to develop and establish an international reputation in environmental research.<p>

<p>

The new four stage competitive scheme will extend and enhance the existing NERC portfolio of<p>

Postdoctoral and Advanced Fellows by including Senior Research Fellows and Research<p>

Professors (Figure 1).  Although the Fellowship scheme provides  a progression through the four<p>

stages from Postdoctoral Research Fellow through to Research Professor, outstanding candidates<p>

of exceptional calibre and potential are open to apply for an award at any of the stages indicated.<p>

<p>

<b>Types of Fellowships Under the New Scheme</b><p>

<p>

<a href="#Sectionb">Postdoctoral</a> Research Fellowships<p>

<p>

For outstanding postdoctoral scientists seeking to make a career transition from postdoctoral<p>

training to becoming independent environmental investigators.  Applicants are advised that some<p>

post-PhD experience is seen as a distinct advantage when seeking a Postdoctoral Research<p>

Fellowship.  Fellowships are normally tenable for three years in the first instance with the<p>

possibility of an extension of up to two further years.  <b>Please see Section B.</b><p>

<p>

<a href="#Sectionc">Advanced</a><b> Research Fellowships </b><p>

<p>

Awarded for up to five years in the first instance to a small number of exceptional research<p>

workers of proven ability and having a high potential to develop into team leaders of international<p>

standing and who do not hold tenured posts at the time of application.  Please see Section C.<p>

<p>

<a href="#Sectiond">Senior</a><b> Research Fellowships</b><p>

<p>

To provide support for five to ten years for a small number of selected environmental scientists of<p>

exceptional research ability who have an established reputation and who are likely to have won,<p>

and to be able to win, NERC or other Research Council Research Grant Support on a continuing<p>

basis.  Please see Section D.<p>

<p>

<a href="#Sectione">Professorial Fellowships</a><p>

<p>

To provide support and long term continuity for proven researchers having well established<p>

international reputations and who wish to devote their working time to research.  Nominations<p>

must receive full support from the host institution.  Please see Section E.<p>

<p>

<a href="#Sectionf">Returner</a><b> Fellowships Scheme</b>Awarded for one year to enable
high-level environmental
scientists to return to their professions<p>

following a career break.  All the information on this scheme can be found in Section F.<p>

     <b>ENVIRONMENTAL SCIENCE RESEARCH CAREERS WITH THE <p>

     NATURAL ENVIRONMENT RESEARCH COUNCIL<p>

     </b><p>

<p>

POSTDOCTORAL RESEARCH FELLOW<p>

3 years (+ 2 extension years)<p>

<p>

Early career development award; to provide further post-doctoral experience and consolidating<p>

experience and expertise; to support outstanding environmental scientists to become independent<p>

investigators.<p>

<p>

Available on a full or part-time basis.<p>

<p>

Up to 1 year tenure can be spent within partner institution/agency.<p>

<p>

                              Career Stage Limits<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>ADVANCED RESEARCH FELLOW*</b><p>

5 years (+ 5 years)<p>

<p>

To enable outstanding early/mid career researchers with high potential to develop into team<p>

leaders of international standing.<p>

<p>

Available on a full or part-time basis.<p>

                              Career Stage Limits<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>SENIOR RESEARCH FELLOW*</b><p>

5 years (+ 5 years)<p>

<p>

To enable proven researchers of international standing at mid/peak career level to devote<p>

themselves to personal research.  <p>

HEI Readership equivalent level.<p>

                              No age limit                            <p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>RESEARCH PROFESSOR*</b><p>

5 years (+ 3 renewable years + 2 years at 50% and 25% funding)<p>

<p>

To provide secure support and long term continuity for proven researchers having well<p>

established international reputations.  Holders must demonstrate the capability of winning NERC<p>

or equivalent Research Council grants gained in open competition.<p>

<p>

                              No age limit<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

* Under approved arrangements up to 2 years of any 5 year award can be spent within a<p>

collaborative institution.<p>

<b>     CONTENTS</b><p>

