<body vlink=#ff0000>
<h3>Targetted Call for New Proposals - NERC Thematic Programme in
Marine Biofouling</h3>
<p>

<h1>ANTIFOULING DEFENCES OF NATURAL MARINE
SURFACES</h1>
<p>
<blockquote>

     Applications are invited to investigate the mechanisms that marine  organisms use to
maintain an epibiont-free surface.  Of particular interest are the processes involved in chemical
defence, and their relative importance to physical mechanisms.  Applications that contain a major
element of natural product antifoulant  screening are unlikely to be considered but proposals that
seek to identify ecological roles for these secondary metabolites, and in particular proposals that
are of an  interdisciplinary nature (e.g. marine chemical ecology and surface chemistry), are
encouraged.  <p>

     A total of 120,000 is available over 2 years.  The deadline for proposals is 1 July 1996
using NERC standard RG1 procedures.  Informal enquiries may be made to Dr A.S. Clare,
Scientific Coordinator of the Thematic Programme (e-mail: <b><A
HREF="mailto:t.clare@pml.ac.uk">t.clare@pml.ac.uk; </a></b> tel: 01752-633341; fax:
01752-633102).  Grant application forms are available from, and completed
proposals (marked  Marine Biofouling in the top left hand corner) should be sent to:<p>
</blockquote>
<p>
<em>
<b>
     NERC Awards &amp; Training,<br>
     Polaris House, <br>
     North Star <br>        
     Tel: (01793) 411546;  fax: (01793) 411616.<p>
<b/>
</em>
Best wishes,<p>
Tony Clare<p>
<b>
