<H1>Exploitation of Research Council Funded Research</H1>
<P>The Research Councils set up a cross Council working group on exploitation
to promote awareness of exploitation following the disbanding of the
Exploitation Scrutiny Group (ESG).  From this group the Councils have set up a
new procedure for reporting exploitation which was underpinned by Council
funding. </P>
<P>The recently collated first year returns allow exploitation to be reported
in the widest sense of the word. There has been a good response from old and new
universities who have demonstrated a wide variety of exploitation activities
from million pound income streams, a portfolio of Teaching Company Schemes to
simple imparting of knowledge to industry which helps set up new processes. </P>
<P>Whilst the reporting mechanism supports  the Councils' argument  to maintain
the level of Science Vote money allocated it will also help to raise the
awareness of the benefits that can be achieved through developing dialogue with
industry.</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="file:///m|/st-atww/image/jetbar.gif" WIDTH="526" HEIGHT="17"></P>
<H1>Understanding Exploitation</H1>
<P>The Councils have jointly published  a leaflet &quot;Guidelines on
Exploitation&quot; which is available from this web site.</P>
<P>NERC has recently published a Handbook on Intellectual Property Management.
A copy is available on request from <A
HREF="mailto:j.peters@wpo.nerc.ac.uk">J.Peters@wpo.nerc.ac.uk</A>
</P></BODY></HTML>
