<body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<body>
<h1>Exploit</h1>
<b>Reporting of Exploitation of Research Results from Research Council Funded Work</b><p>

<p>

NERC, in common with the other Research Councils, requires grant holders to make their best efforts to
exploit the results of their research.  Previous reporting mechanisms have not yielded significant information
about the technology transfer that is occurring.  The Research Councils, in consultation with the Office of
Science and Technology have therefore modified the reporting format and during October 1996 the new
format will be trialed.  The trial form is available in either Word 6.0 (Exploit.doc)for Windows 3.11 or
WordPerfect 6.1 (Exploit.wpd).  These forms are only available from this site until 31st October 1996; this
is the closing date for reporting the returns. The form is to be completed by the <b>Industrial Liaison Office</b>
covering the reporting  year August 1995 to July 1996.  The information required covers all types of
technology transfer and exploitation, described in more detail in the notes section of the form.  The Research
Councils have also issued guidelines for exploitation.  These are available on request from
j.peters@nerc.ac.uk, subject: <i>guidelines for exploitation</i>.<p>

<p>

NERC Technology Interaction Group has also recently published a handbook on Intellectual Property
Management available on request from  

<A HREF="mailto:j.peters@nerc.ac.uk"> Jan Peters </a><p>

<p>

Down load<p>

<p>

Guidelines <a href="guidelin.wpd">WP6.1</a><p>

Guidelines <a href="guidelin.doc">Word</a> 6<p>

Exploitation report <a href="exploit.wpd">WP6.1</a><p>

Exploitation report <a href="exploit.doc">Word6</a>
</body>
</html>
