<TITLE> Awards & Training Home Page</TITLE>
<HEAD>
<body background="/images/tx1004.jpg"><p>
<H1>
<IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif" ALT="NERC" align="top"></H1>
<hr>
<BODY link=#ff0000>
<img SRC="file:///m|/st-atww/image/jetbar.gif" WIDTH="526"
HEIGHT="17">
<HR>
<h1><center>AWARDS AND TRAINING HOME PAGE<center></h1>
 <head/> <left>  
<hr>
<a href="who.htm">A+T contacts</a>
<hr>     
<blockquote>
The NERC Awards and Training Section provides support 
for Research and Training in the environmental sciences.
    Opportunities to obtain support for research and 
training projects are channelled through a number of 
<a href="fundop.htm">Funding Modes</a> and includes <a href="grantapp.htm">Research
Grants</a>, 
 <a href="studfrm.htm">Studentships</a> and <a href="fellbk96.htm">Fellowships</a>.  NERC
also
operates a 
number of Scientific Services, such as Research Vessels,
 Supercomputing etc, which  can be made available in 
conjunction with a research  proposal, or directly, 
through NERC Scientific Services.  
</P><P>
NERC only accepts applications which fall within its 
remit, defined by the mission and Environmental and Natural Resource Issues.

Applicants may wish to discuss the suitability of their 
research with the appropriate Awards and Training Office
 Contact Point. 
</P><P>
The rules, regulations and guidance on how to make an 
appropriate application are 
in the dedicated NERC booklet, which can be 
obtained from the Office Contact Point.
</P><P>
The rules concerning Eligibility to apply for NERC 
funding are strict but kept under regular review.    
Opportunities are not limited to universities, although 
<a href="grantapp.htm">Research Grants</a> and 
<a href="studfrm.htm">Studentships</a> must be based at a 
recognised UK institution.   
</P><P>
Applications for <a href="grantapp.htm">Research Grants</a>,  
<a href="studfrm.htm">Studentships</a> and 
<a href="fellbk96.htm">Fellowships</a>  are considered in regular rounds with 
established Closing Dates.   These cannot be compromised
, but there are Urgency Procedures for critical, 
time-limited opportunities, such as volcanic eruptions.
</P><P>  
All Research Grant and Fellowship proposals are subject to external 
Peer Review, before being graded and ranked by the 
Research Grant and Training Award Committees which make 
recommendations to NERC on scientific 
excellence.   
</P><P>
Training Award allocations are 
made at an annual Training Awards Forum and 
results published in a <A HREF="disply96.htm">Display Notice</A>.
  News on Awards 
and Training Section initiatives and procedures, and 
other general information are included in the <a href="news10.htm">
A & T  Newsletter</a>, produced three times a year.
</P><P>
NERC is alive to the changing demands for trained 
manpower within the research and user communities.  
In response, NERC, in partnership with a range of 
bodies, has initiated a number of  programme and 
projects, now referred to as Thematic Programmes.   
Details of the current portfolio of targetted 
initiatives are addressed under this heading.
<blockquote/>
</P><P></P>
