<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Security of Mail</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H1>Security of Mail</H1> 
<HR>
<P>Internet mail is not secure. It is relatively easily forged and often passes
through several systems between the sender and recipient, where it may be read
and/or altered by privileged users. There are moves to improve the security of
Internet mail but none of these have yet produced products that have met with
universal acceptance or have been widely deployed. At this stage all that we can
say is that you should be aware of the flaws inherent in the medium and should
not send very sensitive material via e-mail.</P>
<P></P>
<HR>
<P><A HREF="http://www.hensa.ac.uk/html-val-svc/"><IMG
SRC="http://www.hensa.ac.uk/html-val-svc/valid_html.gif" ALT="HTML 2.0 Checked!" ALIGN="middle"></A>
<A HREF="http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC="/images/logoicon.gif" ALIGN="middle">
To the NERC home page
</A>
</P>
<P>Author: <I><A HREF="mailto:Alan.G.Cox@ncs.nerc.ac.uk">Alan.Cox@ncs.nerc.ac.uk</A>.</I></P>
<P>Last updated and checked on April 9th 1996.</P>
</BODY></HTML>
