<HEAD>
<TITLE>Announcing your WWW presence</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><H1><IMG SRC="/images/nerc.gif" ALT="NERC" ALIGN="MIDDLE">
Announcing your WWW presence
</H1>
<HR>
<P>
There are a number of different avenues through which one can announce
a presence on the World Wide Web. An obvious one is through
paper-based publications - newsletters and so on - useful for targetted
announcements. For more general announcements the Internet itself is
the obvious medium -
</P>
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/whats-new.html">
NCSA What's New</A> list has a
<A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/whats-new-form.html">form</A>
which you can use to submit announcements.</LI>
<LI>There is the list of
<A HREF="http://www.ja.net/sites/sitevectors.html">servers on JANET</A>
maintained by <A HREF="http://www.ja.net/JANET.html">UKERNA</A>.
</LI>
<LI> The Imperial College list of
<A HREF="http://src.doc.ic.ac.uk/all-uk.html">UK services</A>
has a <A HREF="http://src.doc.ic.ac.uk/cgi-bin/alluk-request.cgi">form</A>
for submitting entries. (Be warned, this service seems to be <I>very</I> slow.)
</LI>
<LI>
The <A HREF="http://info.cern.ch/hypertext/DataSources/bySubject/">WWW Virtual Library</A>
is arranged by subject.
To be added to the library you have to contact the
<A HREF="http://info.cern.ch/hypertext/DataSources/bySubject/Maintainers.html">curator</A>
of the appropriate subject.
</LI>
</UL>
<P>
There are also <I>automata</I> which roam the WWW, discovering servers
and building searchable databases of the web. Some of these have forms
through which you can submit a URL to their database -
</P>
<UL>
<LI>
The <A HREF="http://webcrawler.cs.washington.edu/WebCrawler/WebQuery.html">Web Crawler</A>'s
form is at <A HREF="http://webcrawler.cs.washington.edu/WebCrawler/SubmitURLS.html">Web Crawler URL Submission</A>.
</LI>
<LI>
<A HREF="http://lycos.cs.cmu.edu/">Lycos</A> has its form at
<A HREF="http://lycos.cs.cmu.edu/lycos-register.html">Lycos URL Registration Form</A>.
</LI>
<LI>
The <A HREF="http://www.netgen.com/info/wanderer.html">WWW Wanderer</A>'s
form is
<A HREF="http://www.netgen.com/cgi/addhost">here</A>.
</LI>
</UL>
<P>
Finally, one can also make an announcement to the
<A HREF="news:comp.infosystems.www.announce">comp.infosystems.www.announce</A>
newsgroup. This is a moderated newsgroup; any submissions to the newsgroup
will be vetted and may be edited by the moderator.
</P>
<BR>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  =
"/images/logoicon.gif" ALT="NERC" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
