<HEADER>
<TITLE>NCS at ITE Furzebrook</TITLE>
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1><P>
<H2>Institute of Terrestrial Ecology, Furzebrook Research Station</H2>
<P>
Furzebrook Research Station, part of the Institute of Terrestrial Ecology, forms a core
component of the Terrestrial and Freshwater Directorate.  Furzebrook is situated near
Wareham in Dorset and undertakes a wide range of specialist ecological research. 
Understanding the ecology of different species and of natural and man-made communities
is increasingly important as pressures on our environment continue to rise.  
<P>
The following fields of research are carried out at Furzebrook:-
<UL>
<LI>Population Ecology and Genetics
    <UL>
<LI>Plant Genecology
<LI>     Butterfly and Ant Population Studies
<LI>     Molecular Ecology
</UL>

<LI>Vertebrate Populations and Trophic Ecology
    <UL>
<LI>Migratory Wader Ecology
<LI>     Resident Vertebrate Ecology
</UL>

<LI>Community Ecology
    <UL>
<LI>Heathland Impacts
<LI>     Grassland and Scrub Dynamics
</UL>
<LI>Biometrics and Simulation Modelling
</UL>
In addition, members of staff have considerable experience and expertise in ecological
surveys and environmental impact assessment.
</P>
<HR>
<H3>NERC Computer Services (NCS) at ITE Furzebrook</H3>
<P>
Recently there have been great changes in the computing facilities available at Furzebrook
and a program of training is being undertaken to help the staff reap the full benefits of all
the changes.  NCS supported computer equipment consists of a Local Area Network (LAN)
connecting about 30 PC's to a Novell File server, this provides communal printing facilities,
shared applications and files.  There is one UNIX SUN Workstation for which the primary use
is the development of projects using ARC/INFO, a geographic information system.  Furzebrook
also has access to a MicroVAX II which is located at the <A HREF = "/ncs/riverlab.html">Institute of Freshwater Ecology</A> (IFE)
6 miles away. The LAN is connected to the JANET/UKERNA wide area network allowing
access to other NERC sites, universities and computers both nation and world wide.
<P>
The computing facilities, both hardware and software are supported, on site, by one member
of NCS staff, whose time is split between Furzebrook and <A HREF = "/ncs/riverlab.html">IFE River Laboratory</A>, remotely by
staff based at
<A HREF = "plymouth.html">Plymouth Marine Laboratory</A>
and the NCS centrally based support groups.
<P><HR>
Contact   
<P>
