<TITLE>NCS Resource Management Group</TITLE>
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>

<H2>Resource Management Group</H2>
<P>
The <cite>Resource Management Group</cite> (RMG) brings together a diverse, but necessary,
portfolio of services that underpin the business of <A HREF = "/ncs/">NERC Computer Services</A> (NCS). Many
functions are internal to NCS, but some service the NCS user community directly. <cite>Resource
management</cite> features roles which benefit from an economy-of-scale approach. 
</P><HR>
<P>
RMG also acts as the official contact between NERC and the academic-sector CHEST and NISS
organisations . This facility includes access to discounted PC and other
software deals, and to on-line information resources. Apart from reading external
information, RMG can also arrange for NERC users to distribute information through on-line
bulletin boards, either within NERC, or more widely within the community of Joint Academic
Network (JANET) users.
<P>
Information is available on software
licences and on contract maintenance cover, which is centrally managed by RMG for
computing equipment on institute sites.
<P>
Finally, although training of NCS customers is mainly dealt with under local 
Service Level Agreements, the Training Coordinator within RMG can advise on appropriate
solutions and acts as a central NCS point of contact with institute customers on all training
matters. An RMG library of training/learning materials (videos, CBTs, documentation) is
available, and may be accessed  via local NCS representatives or the Training Coordinator,
(see below).
</P><HR>
<H3>Internal Services</H3>
<P>
RMG carries out a vital role in the internal
administration and operation of the NCS business. 
 The main thrust of the Training Coordinator's role is similarly directed
at needs analysis of NCS staff, and in planning and carrying out programmes to meet those
needs.
<P>
RMG is also responsible for service contract negotiation and management, and software
licensing across NERC, where this is justified by an economy-of-scale approach. The group
maintain and monitor the NCS Financial Plan, as well as contributing  to its formulation.
RMG produce cost allocation statements to institutes summarising the value of NCS services
provided specifically to individual sites. Quarterly statements of NERC-science computing
demand and usage are also published by the Group, as well as a biannual report of NCS
activities in general.
<P>
<HR>
<HR>
