<TITLE>NCS Business Systems Group</TITLE>
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1><P>
<H2>Business Systems group</H2>
<P>
The <A HREF = "/ncs/">NERC Computer Services</A> (NCS) Business Systems Group (BSG) is responsible for the
provision of administrative computing systems to NERC and its institutes.
</P><HR>
<H3>Customer Services</H3>
<P>
Unlike the majority of NCS, on whom NERC scientists rely for the provision of enabling
hardware and software, this group provides applications and support services rather than
just support.
<P>
The group will provide users with technical advice on planning their computing applications,
selection of appropriate software packages and the purchase of associated hardware and
net- working equipment.  Where required, it will install hardware and software and
implement packages to meet the needs of the users in running their business. Additionally,
the group provides documentation, user training and support for all its applications.
<P>
The business areas catered for include accounting and financial applications, asset
management, grant and award payments, human resources, local area networking, and office
systems for Swindon headquarters.  Staff in the group have a good knowledge of not only the
technical, but also the business, aspects of the applications: as such, they are well placed to
provide consultancy and advice on obtaining the best results from the technology in the
office.  In all systems there is a strong emphasis on information delivery.
<P>
The group is fully committed to the PRINCE project management method and is also available
to provide formal project management to any user.
</P><HR>
<H3>Internal Services</H3>
<P>
The group furnishes Director NCS with advice on the financial aspects of managing NCS and
delivers NCS' internal business systems.
<P>
Members of the Business Systems Group participate actively in the NCS quality programme
and the associated quality improvement groups.  They also participate in providing quality
orientated training.
<P><HR>
