<HTML>
<HEADER>
<TITLE>Joint Administrative Computer Service</TITLE>
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1><P>
<H3><FONT COLOR="#8b0000">JACS and BSG have merged to form "Business & Information Services" (B & IS).<BR>
Further information is available</FONT> <A HREF="http://swnta.nsw.ac.uk/bis.htm"><FONT COLOR="#0000ff">here</FONT></A><BR>
</H3>
<HR>
<P>

<h2>Joint Administrative Computer Service</h2>
The Joint Administrative Computer Service (JACS) is funded by the Natural Environment
Research Council (NERC) and the Engineering and Physical Sciences Research Council (EPSRC)
to manage and operate computer facilities in support of the administrative requirements of
the Councils.  The service is used by personnel at most of NERC's sites around the country,
and by EPSRC users. Also, there are users from the Particle Physics and Astronomy Research
Council (PPARC),  on-site in Swindon, at the  Rutherford-Appleton Laboratory, and as far
away as La Palma and Hawaii.
</P><HR>
<h3>Services</h3>
<P>
JACS provides a mainframe service, running IBMs Operating Systems Multiple Virtual
Storage/Enterprise Systems Architecture (MVS/ESA) and Virtual Machine (VM), on an Hitachi
EX44 processor.  This service supports several test and production on-line systems, which
provide end users with access to financial data and Awards and Grants information.  The
applications packages include budgetary control, accounts payable and general ledger.  JACS
manages and operates all aspects of the mainframe service, including security, performance
and charging mechanisms.
<P>
At a time of rapidly changing technology, the Research Councils are formulating Information
System Strategies that will require the provision of services on different platforms.  NERC has
already begun the move to a distributed computing environment (DCE) for their financial and
administrative requirements, and JACS now manages the UNIX boxes that are the beginning
of the Swindon-based DCE.  The functions provided include a mail service, asset register,
diary service, and test facilities for the development of applications, including ORACLE-based
applications.
</P><HR>
<h3>Local Area Networks</h3>
<P>
The demand for more power on the desktop, and the need to share data and packages among
members of a section, has led to the creation of several Local Area Networks (LANs) within
the NERC community in Polaris House and Holbrook House.  JACS provides assistance with the
installation of LANs, including cabling and PC set-up, and also provides on-going support
once the LAN is operational.  Domain controllers containing user data (which is sometimes
sensitive) can be housed in the secure environment offered by the JACS computer room;
integrity and security of the data are therefore easier to ensure.  EPSRC and PPARC are
expected to move towards LAN technology in the very near future.
<P>
PC Support Services within JACS include recommendations of hardware and some software
to be purchased, checking of the hardware once delivered and setting up the PC with any
supported software purchased.  NERC has selected Novell for LAN management and this is
being introduced to LAN users in Polaris House and Holbrook House.  There are currently 200
PCs supported in NERC and 750 PCs in EPSRC and PPARC.
</P><HR>
<h3>Networking</h3>
<P>
The Network Support Group managed by JACS offers a service to all <A HREF = "/ncs/">NCS</A> staff, and their
customers on-site, for assistance in planning, implementing and maintaining Wide Area
Networks (WANs). They also administer the JANET connections, including routers and switches,
which connect the NERC sites into the Joint Academic Network.  In addition, the group
provides a service for LAN cabling local to the Swindon site; this included the major recabling
exercise undertaken in the EPSRC and PPARC wing within Polaris House.
<P><HR>
Contact
<P>
<address>
<P>
Miss Joyce Richmond<br>
Head of JACS <br>
Joint Administrative Computer Service<br>
Polaris House<br>
North Star Avenue<br>
Swindon SN2 1EU<br>
<P>
Tel +44 1793 411624<br>
Tlx 444293 ENVRE G<br>
Fax +44 1793 411504<br>
<P>
j.richmond@ncs.nerc.ac.uk
</P>
