<html>
<header>
<TITLE>NCS Networking</TITLE>
</header>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>
<H2>Networking</H2>
<P>
The implementation of Council's IT strategy is critically dependent on the improvement of
network services.  Significant advances were made during the year in speed of operation,
functionality and ease of management.  Two megabit per second communication links
were brought into service at Keyworth, the James Rennell Centre, Southampton, and
Swindon and modest improvements were possible at other sites as part of the Joint
Network Team (JNT) programme.  Full advantage was taken of the "JIPS" service which
became available over JANET and most NERC sites were provided with equipment to
support the use of IP protocols across the wide-area network.  The addition of this
facility provided users with improved access to supercomputing, easier communication
with international colleagues and better access to information databases.  NCS used this
enhanced functionality to improve the productivity of its applications and systems
support groups and to provide remote monitoring of network performance.  Progress was
made in other aspects of network management and the integration of the network
support team within the JACS operation made possible the provision of improved help
desk facilities for progressing network problems.  The full benefits of remote network
management will be realised when structured cabling systems are installed at all NERC
sites.  Substantial progress was made during the year and seven sites are now equipped to
this standard.
</P>
<br>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  = "/images/logoicon.gif" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
</body>
</html>


