<html>
<header><TITLE>NCS Resource Management and Consultancy
</TITLE>
</header>
<body>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>
<H2>Resource Management and Consultancy</H2>
<P>
Following the transfer of Mr Darwall to the newly created post of NSS Business
Development Manager, the resource management and consultancy groups were merged
under the overall direction of Dr David Farmer.  Improvements were made to internal
systems for managing financial allocations, enabling better use to be made of the
resources available.  Costs were contained effectively without impacting the perceived
quality of the service.  Improved financial information also led to a more productive
discussion with directorates in the annual business planning process.  
<P>
Following the appointment of a full-time training coordinator, a comprehensive training
programme was prepared and implemented.  Users recognise that NCS is committed to
providing staff with skills appropriate to their support needs and this was reflected in the
results of the Customer Satisfaction Survey.
<P>
NCS consultants took part in a wide range of activities and provided advice on both
strategic and technical issues.  Draft Information Systems Strategies were developed for
the Marine &amp; Atmospheric Sciences Directorate and the Terrestrial &amp; Freshwater
Directorate and the Information Technology Strategy was finalised with substantial input
from members of the consultancy team.  Support was provided for the system
replacement programme at Wallingford and a new computer system at the Institute of
Virology &amp; Environmental Microbiology.  NCS consultants provided direct support for NERC
community programmes by coordinating the use of national supercomputing facilities
within the capacity allocated to NERC, and through technical support for advanced
developments in supercomputing and remote sensing.
<P>
Good progress was made in developing the NERC Data Catalogue and a prototype system
was demonstrated to Data Centre managers and members of the Information Systems
Advisory Committee.  The production system will become operational in the second half of
1993.
</P>
<br>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  = "/images/logoicon.gif" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
</body>
