<header>
<TITLE>NCS Operating Systems</TITLE>
</headr>
<body>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>
<H2>Operating Systems</H2>
<P>
Following a lengthy period of consultation, the Services and Facilities Committee endorsed
the Information Technology (IT) Strategy prepared by NCS.  The strategy sets out a model
for the deployment of distributed computing based on compliance with industry
standards.  Institutes continued to invest heavily in computing equipment in accordance
with this strategy and in so doing indicated their confidence in NCS to provide effective
system management.  Operating system support focused on a number of activities
including refining the NERC file structure (for Unix systems) and improving installation
procedures and system backup facilities.  By focusing on these areas, NCS staff were able
to demonstrate their ability to install and commission new equipment in a cost-effective
and timely manner and to provide ongoing support through the network. 
<P>
The integration of personal computers within the distributed computing environment is
an important feature of the IT strategy and the evaluation of software to achieve this aim
was a key technical issue.  Novell Netware was selected as the lead product for PC
integration and steps were taken to provide the appropriate organisation and skills
training for Council-wide deployment.
</P>
<br>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  = "/images/logoicon.gif" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
</body>
