<html>
<header>
<TITLE>NCS Applications</TITLE>
</header>
<body>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>
<H2>Applications</H2>
Ongoing investment in new hardware led to a steady demand for the installation of
standard software products.  The major software packages, including ORACLE, UNIRAS, SAS
and NAG, were all updated to the latest release level and deployed throughout NERC on a
wide range of hardware platforms.  To improve the productivity of support staff a decision
was taken to contract support for the HORIZON product to the supplier, Laser-Scan.  At
the same time, the deployment of licences was reviewed to concentrate use at the Monk's
Wood site.  This change made it possible to focus support for geographical information
systems on ARC/INFO reflecting the widespread use of this product within NERC.  The
support of software products across a wide range of hardware and operating system
platforms requires careful management.  Progress was made in defining an Operational
Requirement for a Change Management System and an implementation project was put in
hand.  NERC has access to 'academic use' software under terms negotiated by CHEST and
a number of products, including PVWAVE, AVS, INTERLEAF and PAPYRUS, were installed to
meet particular user requirements.  NCS has a commitment to provide users with training
in the use of applications packages and the extent to which this can be addressed is
specified within Service Level Agreements.  NCS staff provided over 200 days of training to
users in the use of software products, in addition to informal training at local level.
<br>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  = "/images/logoicon.gif" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
</body>
