<header>
<TITLE>NCS Business Systems</TITLE>
</header>
<body>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>
<H2>Business Systems</H2><P>
No major changes were made to the accounting and personnel systems; routine support
ensured that business applications ran smoothly throughout the year.  A number of
small-scale projects for customers were brought to a successful conclusion and technical
assistance was provided to Establishments Division in making a business case for a new
Human Resource Management System.  New office systems were developed to provide
Swindon-based staff with electronic mail and other facilities previously supplied by the
IBM system at Wallingford.  These make use of the CLIQ software product from Quadraton
running on an IBM RS6000 system under the operational control of JACS.  Assistance was
provided to users in Headquarters in transferring applications from the Wallingford
system.  Some progress was made in developing a Management Information System for
NCS use.  Responsibility for providing PC support to staff in the Headquarters building was
transferred to JACS as part of a move to improve efficiency.  A number of departmental
server systems were relocated to the JACS computer room to improve operational control
and Help Desk facilities were extended to include network problems.  The IBM mainframe
and its associated discs were replaced with a Hitachi EX44 system early in the year to
support a higher level of business processing activity.  The replacement was accomplished
without significant interruption to the service.
</P>
<br>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  = "/images/logoicon.gif" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
</body>
</html>


