<header>
<TITLE>NCS External Activities</TITLE>
</header>
<body>
<IMG SRC  = "/images/ncs.gif">
<HR>
<H1></H1>
<H2>External Activities
</H2>
As in previous years, NCS made an active contribution to the development of computer
services within the academic community.  Formal liaison was maintained through the
Head of Service as NERC's assessor to the Information Systems Committee (ISC) of the
Universities Funding Council until its disbandment at the end of the year.  In preparation
for the transfer of its responsibilities to the Joint Information Systems Committee of the
Higher Education Funding Councils, the ISC established an Advisory Committee for
Networking (ACN) to consider future management arrangements for JANET.  The Head of
Service and the Head of JACS contributed to discussions on connection policy and service
definitions through sub-committees of the ACN.
<P>
NCS staff (Dr Hopper, Mr Groom and Mrs Morrison) provided consultancy services and
advice to CHEST on the evaluation of Image Analysis software and the purchase of data. 
NERC continued to benefit from the favourable terms under which CHEST products are
made available to the academic and research community and informal contacts were
maintained on a range of other issues.  Responsibility for the provision of national
supercomputing facilities rests with the ABRC and is administered through SERC.  NERC is
represented within the committee structures which oversee this activity and the Head of
Service is one of two representatives on the Supercomputing Management Committee. 
During the year the committee reviewed the case for investment in supercomputing to
meet the "grand challenges" in scientific research.  A report on research requirements
for high-performance computing was produced by a scientific working group under the
chairmanship of Professor Catlow.  The NERC contribution to this important report was
prepared by Dr Farmer.  The evaluation of performance is an important factor in the
procurement of supercomputer systems and NCS has particular expertise in this area.  
Dr Ashworth continued to develop benchmarking codes to represent NERC's future
modelling requirements and contributed to the work of the Supercomputing Management 
Committee through its benchmark working group.  
<P>
Display material was supplied to Corporate Affairs for exhibition at Expo '92 in Seville and
at the British Association for the Advancement of Science meeting in Southampton.  Four
editions of 'NERC Computing' were published with contributions from NCS staff, NERC
colleagues and external authors.  Articles covered a wide range of technical subjects,
including the application of computing to specific scientific projects.  The editor, Mrs
Melia, completed her two-year stewardship during which favourable comments were
received from many quarters.
</P>
<br>
<A HREF = "http://www.nerc.ac.uk/"><IMG SRC  = "/images/logoicon.gif" align=middle>To the NERC home page</A>
</body>
