<Title>Literate</title>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR=#99FFFF>
<CENTER>
<H1>Literacy<BR>
An Obtainable Goal</H1>
</center>

It is difficult to go anywhere without hearing or seeing the phrase <B>"Literacy"</B>. Everyone wants it, for themselves, for their children, for their students. Unfortunately, no one seems to agree on what it means.<P>

The two selections below are our extended definitions of what <B>"Literacy"</B> means in the context of educational achievement. We state that the objective of education is to produce <I>communicative, cooperating, and contributing adults.</I> An adult who is not <B>"Literate"</B> will not be an effective <I>communicator.</I><P>
The one thing that the teachers at Macro Press do not use is "Buzz" words. We mean what we say, and say what we mean.<P><P>
<FONT SIZE=5>

<HR>
<DT><A HREF="numbers.htm" TARGET="main" >Numbers Don't Lie??? </A><BR>

<HR>
<DT><A HREF="sciliter.htm" TARGET="main" >Science Literacy??? </A><BR>





