<TR>
<TH COLSPAN=3>TEACHING THOUGTS</TH>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD COLSPAN=2>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>"Begin now to study the things in your own yard, going from the known to the nearest related unknown."</I> George Washington Carver</B><P>
<FONT SIZE=3>
Known facts (History) are important stepping stones to future knowledge, but if they are not related (in-context) to what is known, they are easily forgotten. Our increasingly complex and technical society can not afford this loss. The children enter Kindergarten eager to learn and grow. Now, we can help them achieve their exciting, and <B>vital</B>, goal with in-context, hands-on learning. Real Science education is <I>learning how to learn</I> more effectively.<P>
</TD

<TD>
<B>EXPLORING SCIENCE</B> is a K-6 program designed to meet the broad spectrum (Special Needs to Gifted, including ESL) needs of America's elementary classrooms by rigorous adherence to the 1995 <I>National Science Education Standards</I>[NSES] (official adoption Dec. 15, 1995). For simplicity, each grade level (classroom) pricing is identical. <P>
