<TITLE>Macro Press</TITLE>
<P>

<B><I>"... engineering consists is the art of doing well with one dollar which any bumbler can do with two, after a fashion."</I>
<P>Arthur M. Wellington</B><P>
<P>

<DT><A HREF="weare.htm">The Backgrounds of the EXPLORING SCIENCE Authors</A>
<DD>Science Education is more than presenting knowledge. It takes experienced teachers to make that information usable by the students. Further, it takes experienced mentor/master teachers to write materials that provide automatic in-servicing while they are being used by classroom teachers.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="whydid.htm">The Why of EXPLORING SCIENCE. </A>
<DD>Why is a wonderful question. Every child uses it a lot - so does every scientist! The classroom teacher/authors addressed the NEEDS of their classrooms.
<P>

<DT><A HREF="gradeorg.htm">View the Organization of an Appropriate Curriculum </A>
<DD>This report presents the organization of a K-6 curriculum that was written by active elementary teachers to accomplish the new US National Science Standards.
<P>

<H1> Teacher's Students Win Again!</H1>
Leigh Hoven-Severson's have competed three years in a row in the <BR> 
NASA/NSTA Space Science Involvement Program<BR>
(Spacecraft design contest - grades 3 to 5)<P>

<B>Results:</B><BR>
As a third grade teacher:<BR>
1994- <B>1+2</B> in California, <B>2</B> in nation<BR>
1995-  <B>1+3</B> in California.<BR>
1996-  As a fifth grade teacher:<BR> <DD><B>1</B> in California, 3 in nation.<P>

using the new 1995 National Science Education Standards.<BR>

The standards work, even for the non-gifted third graders!<P>

Three things are clear:<BR>
<OL>
<LI>Young students can infer and problem solve.
<LI>TRUE science education teaches students how to learn.
<LI>Teachers concentrate on teaching, publishers on profits, and bureaucracies on positions.
</OL><P>

Upon careful study, it is vary clear that <B>any</B> fifth grade teachers students can easily defeat Leigh Hoven-Severson's students. All they need to do is teach science process, thematic science, and integrated curriculum.<P>

The easiest way to meet the new National Science Education Standards is to use EXPLORING SCIENCE (K-6) like Leigh does.<P><P>

