Governor James B. Hunt<BR>
Raleigh, NC<P><P>


Dear Governor:<P>
I have read the story of the report issued by the commission on education that you headed. Everything listed in the story is popular belief. However, <B>a necessary precondition exists for the study conclusions to be accurate.</B> The generally available curriculum materials must be both appropriate to the desired outcome of the given class work, and written to support the teachers.<P>

