	<P>
A professional, in any trade, is measured by the quality of his/her tools. Auto mechanics do not use only screw drivers and pliers. Teachers today receive "platinum books" and "gold toys". They do not receive supportive curriculum!<P>
<HR>
My favorite teacher has a reason that explains why the "problems" exist in education today. She says, "The educators rightly believe that children learn the same way that adults do. HOWEVER, they wrongly believe that children can be taught the same way. They IGNORE the fact that children lack the experiential facts necessary to fill in the holes that exist when short cuts and partial information is given.<P>

Her students are able to win the NASA/NSTA SSIP because she is supported by an <B><I>ELEMENTARY TEACHER WRITTEN</I></B> science curriculum. The authors recognize the basic truths that "educators" seem to ignore, or are unaware of.<P>

<HR>
<B><I>When ALL curriculum that our children are exposed to meet this standard, they will truly be "first in the world".</I></B> EXPLORING SCIENCE is merely an example of what can, and should, be done, IN ALL CURRICULUM AREAS. It is sad that a small group of experienced teachers had to put in massive time and risk their retirement funds to put the program together. But, no longer can it be said that the problems are TV, the children, the parents, or the teachers. The proof is clear, blame publishers and administrators, who are too busy "doing their job" to make sure that their teachers have the supportive curriculum necessary to teach the children. They have forgotten, <A HREF="howkids.htm"> "And, how are the children?"</A><P>
<HR>


Sincerely,<P>


Larry L. Severson<P>
